{"id": "3571", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3571", "title": "Twin Seas", "text": "The Twin Seas are, in fact, a single waterway divided only by a narrow neck that separates the western and eastern halves of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. The northerly sea acts as a barrier between &lt;a href=\"Aranoch\"&gt;Aranoch&lt;/a&gt; to the west and &lt;a href=\"Kehjistan\"&gt;Kehjistan&lt;/a&gt; to the east. The southerly sea leads into the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Ocean\"&gt;Great Ocean&lt;/a&gt;, and is the location of the &lt;a href=\"Skovos%20Isles\"&gt;Skovos Isles&lt;/a&gt;.\n Violent storms sometimes occur in the Seas, and are sailed by pirates. In the past, these pirates lay siege to &lt;a href=\"Tran%20Athulua\"&gt;Tran Athulua&lt;/a&gt;. Pirates remain an issue in the present. To this end, sailors from &lt;a href=\"Lut%20Gholein\"&gt;Lut Gholein&lt;/a&gt; distill the waters of the Twin Seas and apply the bright blue mixture to their sails in order to blend in and avoid detection by pirates."}
