{"id": "20912", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20912", "title": "Tzo Krin's Gaze", "text": "Tzo Krin's Gaze is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Spirit%20Stones\"&gt;spirit stone&lt;/a&gt; for the in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60 to drop.\nThe unique affix makes the &lt;a href=\"Wave%20of%20Light\"&gt;Wave of Light&lt;/a&gt; a ranged attack, making it land atop of enemy (or target location) anywhere within the screen borders instead of right next to the Monk. Even the Explosive Light rune is affected, spreading fire streams from the impact point above the target. The stone also comes with an extremely large increase in damage to the skill, as a Primary Magic Property in addition to the typical 4 other Primary properties.\nStats (Level 70).\nThis is one of the few items with five Primary properties. The large increase to Wave of Light damage cannot be changed via &lt;a href=\"Enchanting\"&gt;Enchanting&lt;/a&gt;, and also makes single-skill damage bonuses unavailable for any of the other four Primary properties."}
{"id": "3051", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3051", "title": "T\u00far D\u00falra", "text": "T\u00far D\u00falra is located in &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0and is the greatest of all the &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; Colleges. It is here that stands the magnificent oak tree, &lt;a href=\"Gl%C3%B3r-an-Fh%C3%A1idha\"&gt;Gl\u00f3r-an-Fh\u00e1idha&lt;/a&gt;.\u00a0Rune work is also practiced here.\nIn-game.\nT\u00far D\u00falra is explorable in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". The great oak and its surrounding druid college were besieged by &lt;a href=\"Astaroth\"&gt;Astaroth&lt;/a&gt;, and the ruins are initially a &lt;a href=\"Stronghold\"&gt;Stronghold&lt;/a&gt; which the Wanderer must cleanse of demons and tormented Druid spirits.\nAdditionally, players are directed to T\u00far D\u00falra for an important class mechanic. Once the area is reclaimed, Druids can find four animal spirits here, each of which provides four different boons to choose from and improve the Druid's skills. Boons are unlocked by collecting Druidic Spirit Offerings, items which drop from monsters all over Sanctuary. Players can initially have one boon from each spirit, and eventually can take a fifth boon once the maximum amount of Offerings have been made."}
