{"id": "38869", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38869", "title": "Undying Rage", "text": "Undying Rage\u00a0is a Defensive skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", working similarly to &lt;a href=\"Nerves%20of%20Steel\"&gt;Nerves of Steel&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nUndying Rage is a passive effect similar to those found in the previous game. Upon dying, it gives a small window of time to kill any enemy (not necessarily the one who actually delivered the killing blow to the Barbarian). If successful, the character's death is undone. Can only happen once every 2.9 minutes.\nWhile under this effect, the Barbarian is reduced to 0 Life, and will not take any further damage, but can still be affected by &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt;.\nAdditional Ranks increase the amount of healing and reduce the &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt;, but do not prolong the window."}
