{"id": "20508", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20508", "title": "Unity", "text": "Unity is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"rings\"&gt;ring&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 60 to drop.\nThe unique legendary effect is essentially a &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Traits%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Health Link&lt;/a&gt; affix for players, splitting unsaved &lt;a href=\"damage\"&gt;damage&lt;/a&gt; taken between all players and &lt;a href=\"follower\"&gt;follower&lt;/a&gt;s within 100 yards who are also wearing Unity rings. The exact damage taken is determined by the defenses of the character actually hit, so those taking damage through the link do not benefit from their own protections. A character can be killed by the damage their ally is taking. Dead characters do not take part in the link in either direction.\nIf either linked target is completely &lt;a href=\"immune\"&gt;immune&lt;/a&gt; to damage (or at least to that &lt;a href=\"elemental%20damage\"&gt;elemental damage&lt;/a&gt; type), the immune character's hits taken do \"not\" get transferred to others. However, hits the other characters take still get transferred to the immune character in the usual proportion, where that damage is immediately cancelled, acting as overall &lt;a href=\"Damage%20Reduction\"&gt;Damage Reduction&lt;/a&gt; for every hit.\nWhen Unity is used by both the player and a &lt;a href=\"Follower\"&gt;Follower&lt;/a&gt; with the Legendary follower item that prevents them from dying (, or ), it effectively doubles the player's own &lt;a href=\"Toughness\"&gt;Toughness&lt;/a&gt;, on par with other endgame Damage Reduction powers. However, this trick does not work in &lt;a href=\"multiplayer\"&gt;multiplayer&lt;/a&gt;.\nStats (Level 60).\nUnity grants a good damage bonus against &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Monsters\"&gt;Elite Monsters&lt;/a&gt;, with that bonus normally unable to roll on a ring, although the amount is less than the 's. That Magic Property cannot be replaced by &lt;a href=\"enchanting\"&gt;enchanting&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "24849", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24849", "title": "Unity (Diablo III Skill)", "text": "Unity\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0passive skill, unlocked at level 64. It is a reincorporation of the pre-2.0 &lt;a href=\"Guiding%20Light\"&gt;Guiding Light&lt;/a&gt; skill.\nIn-game.\nPredictably, this skill is most useful to a Monk in large multiplayer games: in a solo game or in a group of two players, most of the time, it can reach up to 10% (&lt;a href=\"Mystic%20Ally\"&gt;Mystic Ally&lt;/a&gt; + &lt;a href=\"follower\"&gt;follower&lt;/a&gt; or second party member). &lt;a href=\"Inna%27s%20Mantra\"&gt;Inna's Mantra&lt;/a&gt; set also benefits greatly from it.\nNote that to reach the full 20% effect, at least one affected player must have a summoned minion, otherwise even in a full group the effect will not go above 15%.\nDamage buff is not multiplicative to other similar modifiers."}
