{"id": "24765", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24765", "title": "Unstable Anomaly", "text": "Unstable Anomaly is a\u00a0\u00a0passive skill, unlocked at level 60.\nIn-game.\nUnstable Anomaly, for quite obvious reasons, is a mandatory passive for &lt;a href=\"Hardcore\"&gt;Hardcore&lt;/a&gt; characters.\n60 seconds recharge time is unaffected by the &lt;a href=\"Cooldown\"&gt;Cooldown&lt;/a&gt; Reduction attribute, regardless of source, but is reset if the Wizard dies naturally.\nUnlike other similar abilities, it does not heal the character back, even to 1 Life. Instead, it prevents the attack that would otherwise kill the hero, as if it has never even happened, and shields them afterwards.\nKnockback radius is approximately 60 yards, farther than any other Knockback effect in game, enough to send \"all\" nearby enemies flying (often into the walls) and free enough space for the Wizard to escape.\nLife-saving effect of &lt;a href=\"Firebird%27s%20Finery\"&gt;Firebird's Finery&lt;/a&gt; set triggers before the Unstable Anomaly."}
