{"id": "44481", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44481", "title": "Untameable Wilds", "text": "The &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Circle\"&gt;Circle&lt;/a&gt; is an ancient coven of witches originating from &lt;a href=\"Sharval\"&gt;Sharval&lt;/a&gt;. One of their &lt;a href=\"Nisza\"&gt;members&lt;/a&gt; makes an appearance in &lt;a href=\"The%20Chainbreakers\"&gt;The Chainbreakers&lt;/a&gt; quest in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe Untameable Wilds Witches are familiar with &lt;a href=\"Familiar%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;Familiars&lt;/a&gt;. They sign spiritual contracts with them, binding them to mortals.\nHistory.\nLong ago, the &lt;a href=\"Nightgrant\"&gt;Nightgrant&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Circle\"&gt;Circle&lt;/a&gt; made a pact with a &lt;a href=\"Voidwound\"&gt;group of demons&lt;/a&gt;, seeking to gain knowledge of the dark. Unfortunately, the demons demanded a hefty price in sacrifice to stay their hands for a single generation. The , together with the &lt;a href=\"Waning%20Sentinel\"&gt;Waning Sentinel&lt;/a&gt; circles opposed the pact but the Nightgrant, empowered by their masters silenced them. After a long battle in which many of them were killed by &lt;a href=\"Catarag%20the%20Strangling%20Sun\"&gt;Catarag&lt;/a&gt;, the Untameable Wilds were victorious. Seven witches \u2014 &lt;a href=\"Gwerith\"&gt;Gwerith&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Mablia\"&gt;Mablia&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Leweke\"&gt;Leweke&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wledyr\"&gt;Wledyr&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Howel\"&gt;Howel&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ithel\"&gt;Ithel&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Seysild\"&gt;Seysild&lt;/a&gt; \u2014 sacrificed their lives to power the wards that sealed Catarag.\nUsing their bodies as baits, the remaining Voidwound were trapped. Before the corruption could poison their bodies, they ventured to an &lt;a href=\"Voidwound%20Cage\"&gt;island&lt;/a&gt; and using the boughs of moonlit trees and the stone and iron of fallen stars, the Circle fashioned a prison for the Voidwound. With light of the moon, they sealed the them and sank the prison beneath the waves. At the end, the once great Circle was reduced to ten witches. \nSince then, they were responsible for the protection and maintenance of the Voidwound's prison.\nThe Chainbreakers.\nSometime around late &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231272\"&gt;1272&lt;/a&gt;, the island where the Voidwound's prison was located was attacked by the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt;. The prison was damaged and &lt;a href=\"Nisza\"&gt;the Wardkeeper&lt;/a&gt; driven back. Using the opportunity, the Voidwound freed themselves. Fortunately the Wardkeeper, with the help of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; were able to hunt them down\nShardstorms.\nLater, &lt;a href=\"Shardstorms\"&gt;Shardstorms&lt;/a&gt; began surging from the &lt;a href=\"Dreadlands\"&gt;Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt; to most of the &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary%23Lands%20of%20the%20West\"&gt;western continent&lt;/a&gt;. The Prima saw a vision of the threat they posed and sent &lt;a href=\"Seysild%20the%20Surveyor\"&gt;the Surveyor&lt;/a&gt; to calm the land."}
