{"id": "49583", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=49583", "title": "Update Promotional Event", "text": "Update promotional events are time-limited events in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They offer daily tasks to complete, and on certain days of the event the background picture updates to reveal a teaser for an upcoming update.\nGameplay.\nDuring the event, XP gained from levelling up the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20Pass\"&gt;Battle Pass&lt;/a&gt; is increased by 100%.\nThe daily tasks are:\nRewards for logging in on certain days:\nPost-update.\nSome major updates also have a post-update event, with various tasks usually related to the content of the update. These tasks award tokens (usually called Champions' Commendations) and most tasks are usually repeatable, but there is a limit of 1200 tokens earned per week, which resets in 7 days counting from the release of the update. The collected tokens can be spent on the following rewards:\nHistory.\nIn Grim Preparation, the tasks also rewarded one scroll each, and the cumulative login rewards required a certain number of scrolls (2, 4 and 6 respectively)."}
{"id": "15472", "revid": "36180155", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=15472", "title": "Upgrading", "text": "Upgrading or \"upping\" in \"\" changes an item's base type from basic to exceptional, or from exceptional to elite. This can be done with &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; armor or weapons, and can extend the usefulness of some items to higher levels. Furthermore, &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;Rune Words&lt;/a&gt; are counted as Unique Items, though they cannot be upgraded nonetheless.\nHoradric Cube Recipes for Upgrading Items.\nFor example, &lt;a href=\"Bonesnap\"&gt;Bonesnap&lt;/a&gt; is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; which has a hefty chance of crushing blow, resistance bonuses and can have excellent enhanced damage. For lack of a better item, someone can choose to upgrade the item type to a &lt;a href=\"War%20Club\"&gt;War Club&lt;/a&gt;. It will still have all the properties of Bonesnap, but have the War Club's damage, making it more useful for Nightmare and Hell Difficulty levels. That is not all, however. Bonesnap could be upgraded again to an &lt;a href=\"Ogre%20Maul\"&gt;Ogre Maul&lt;/a&gt;, making its base damage about 300% higher than the Maul item type and having its damage capabilities calculated off that. If this Bonesnap had 232% enhanced damage, as an Ogre Maul it would do between 255-351.\nAs another example, someone could decide that &lt;a href=\"Tiamat%27s%20Rebuke\"&gt;Tiamat's Rebuke&lt;/a&gt; rates being upgraded for them, and to boost their resistances, they asked &lt;a href=\"Larzuk\"&gt;Larzuk&lt;/a&gt; to install a socket and they put a perfect diamond to in it. They put a Lem and a Ko rune along with a spare perfect diamond in the cube with the shield. After hitting the Transmute button, they will have a &lt;a href=\"Monarch\"&gt;Monarch&lt;/a&gt; shield with the properties of Tiamat's Rebuke, complete with the socket and the diamond installed. Its defense will range anywhere from 319-444."}
{"id": "38851", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38851", "title": "Upheaval", "text": "Upheaval\u00a0is a Fury skill used by\u00a0\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", loosely based on &lt;a href=\"Seismic%20Slam\"&gt;Seismic Slam&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThis skill works as a long-ranged variant of the , hitting a long line instead of concentrated area, but for less damage.\nRequires a &lt;a href=\"Two-Handed\"&gt;Two-Handed&lt;/a&gt; weapon to be equipped and switches to it when used.\nCounts as Berserker skill."}
{"id": "3494", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3494", "title": "Upper Kurast", "text": "Upper Kurast is the part of the city located between the &lt;a href=\"Kurast%20Bazaar\"&gt;Kurast Bazaar&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Kurast%20Causeway\"&gt;Kurast Causeway&lt;/a&gt;. \nAs its name suggests, Upper Kurast is the upper most portion of &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;. Among its temples are entrances to the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Temple\"&gt;Forgotten Temple&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Reliquary\"&gt;Forgotten Reliquary&lt;/a&gt;, small optional dungeons. The monsters found within Upper Kurast are usually the same as the ones encountered in the Bazaar and Lower &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt;.\nThere are also entrances to the &lt;a href=\"Sewers%20%28Act%20III%29\"&gt;Sewers&lt;/a&gt; and there is a &lt;a href=\"waypoint\"&gt;waypoint&lt;/a&gt; present."}
