{"id": "48582", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48582", "title": "Vampire Lord Zir", "text": "Lord Zir was an ancient &lt;a href=\"vampire\"&gt;vampire&lt;/a&gt; and former &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nEarly Life.\nZir was among the &lt;a href=\"Firstborn\"&gt;Firstborn&lt;/a&gt; nephalem. In the days of the Ancients, Zir gathered his kinsmen and made an offer of power.\nAfter &lt;a href=\"the%20Purge\"&gt;the Purge&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Inarius\"&gt;Inarius&lt;/a&gt; tampered with the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, robbing the Firstborn of the power they'd once enjoyed. Zir and his cohort reacted negatively to this, and for their actions, were imprisoned in the underground &lt;a href=\"City%20of%20the%20Ancients\"&gt;City of the Ancients&lt;/a&gt;. He slumbered under Sanctuary, waiting to enact his twisted plan to rule over all.\nAt some point prior to his imprisonment, Zir feasted on &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; and achieved immortality. \nSeason of Blood.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231336\"&gt;1336&lt;/a&gt; Zir awoke from long slumber. He led a vampire cult and dispatched a vampire army under the command of the &lt;a href=\"Bloodseekers\"&gt;Bloodseekers&lt;/a&gt;, under orders to conquer &lt;a href=\"Scosglen\"&gt;Scosglen&lt;/a&gt;, the &lt;a href=\"Dry%20Steppes\"&gt;Dry Steppes&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Hawezar\"&gt;Hawezar&lt;/a&gt;. This campaign was referred to as the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Harvest\"&gt;Blood Harvest&lt;/a&gt;. He would not stop until he had bled Sanctuary dry. and his followers were ordered to gather &lt;a href=\"blood\"&gt;blood&lt;/a&gt; for a terrible ritual. His cult members hid themselves in numerous places, operating within human &lt;a href=\"town\"&gt;town&lt;/a&gt;s, ensnaring victims and/or sending them off to areas where vampires could ambush them. He sealed off the City of the Ancients.\nWhen was bitten by a vampire, Zir was able to talk to them from afar, but the Wanderer did not change into a vampire for some reason. Zir later summoned &lt;a href=\"Oren\"&gt;Oren&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Tomb%20of%20Hallows\"&gt;Tomb of Hallows&lt;/a&gt;. Oren believed this to be a reward for sending the Wanderer to be bitten, but when Oren entered the tomb, he was executed by Zir's vampires, despite his pleas to be given another chance. &lt;a href=\"Erys\"&gt;Erys&lt;/a&gt; later theorized that Zir had ordered Oren killed because of her presence and the Wanderer's. That he'd left a trail for them to follow, complicating Zir's plans. With Oren dead, at least one loose end was taken care of.\nErys left the tomb, while the Wanderer continued their descent. It was at this moment that Zir resumed his telepathic communication with the Wanderer. He taunted them as they descended, before they arrived in the tomb's depths, where Zir appeared as a bloody apparition before them. He declared that the Wanderer would join his Blood Seekers, but the Wanderer refused. Perturbed, Zir demanded to know why the Wanderer hadn't turned into a vampire, before he realized that the blood of &lt;a href=\"Lilith\"&gt;Lilith&lt;/a&gt; they carried inside them was preventing their transformation. Still, it didn't matter. The Wanderer might not turn into a vampire, but they would thirst for blood all the same, and the more they thirsted, the more they would understand.\nThrough his link with the Wanderer, Zir observed them kill a number of his Blood Seekers. Unperturbed, Zir's campaign against the living intensified. &lt;a href=\"Erys\"&gt;Erys&lt;/a&gt; theorized that Zir's army was making a \"big push\" in order to gather the remaining blood required to ensure Zir's \"ascension.\" While Zir's armies were defeated, Erys feared that Zir would rally his remaining legions to gather the blood he needed. To that end, the Wanderer entered the City of the Ancients and fought their way to Zir themselves. Zir taunted them from afar until the Wanderer confronted him directly. Zir was slain in the ensuing battle.\nLegacy.\nWhile Zir had been killed, his &lt;a href=\"thrall\"&gt;thrall&lt;/a&gt;s remained. &lt;a href=\"Erys\"&gt;Erys&lt;/a&gt; feared that the strongest would try to claim his throne, and that the killings would continue.\nIn-game.\nZir was the main antagonist of \"&lt;a href=\"Season%20of%20Blood\"&gt;Season of Blood&lt;/a&gt;\" in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\". He contacted the player throughout the season, and is fought at the end of the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"A%20Serpent%20Cornered\"&gt;A Serpent Cornered&lt;/a&gt;.\"\nZir can be summoned again in &lt;a href=\"the%20Darkened%20Way\"&gt;the Darkened Way&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Fractured%20Peaks\"&gt;Fractured Peaks&lt;/a&gt;. Nine &lt;a href=\"Exquisite%20Blood\"&gt;Exquisite Blood&lt;/a&gt; must be obtained to summon him. Upon defeat, Zir can drop the &lt;a href=\"Diadem%20of%20the%20Ancient\"&gt;Diadem of the Ancient&lt;/a&gt; (a cosmetic helm), in addition to the following &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;Unique Items&lt;/a&gt;:"}
