{"id": "41167", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41167", "title": "Dark Houses", "text": "Dark Houses were a gameplay function of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". &lt;a href=\"Shadows\"&gt;Shadows&lt;/a&gt; players could form and join Dark Houses, which were akin to guilds from MMOs. The Dark Houses were all effectively in competition with each other, fighting to be at the top of the guild rankings. The more each Dark House's members were actively engaged with Shadows activities, the higher their house would be in the rankings.\nThe Houses were replaced by the &lt;a href=\"Cycle%20of%20Strife\"&gt;Cycle of Strife&lt;/a&gt;'s \"dark clan\" system."}
