{"id": "13005", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=13005", "title": "Dark Warrior (Assassin Build)", "text": "The Dark Warrior is an &lt;a href=\"Assassin%20builds\"&gt;Assassin build&lt;/a&gt; with many variants that focuses on &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Disciplines\"&gt;Shadow Disciplines&lt;/a&gt;. Using skills such as &lt;a href=\"Venom\"&gt;Venom&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Master\"&gt;Shadow Master&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Warrior\"&gt;Shadow Warrior&lt;/a&gt; is core to the build."}
{"id": "2641", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2641", "title": "Dark Wood", "text": "The Dark Wood is a forest located in northern &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Dark Wood is thickest in its south. The largest (and oldest) trees of the wood grow here. The &lt;a href=\"Justinian%20Road\"&gt;Justinian Road&lt;/a&gt; connects it to &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nThe Dark Wood has long served as a shortcut for merchants traveling through northern Khanduras.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231264\"&gt;1264&lt;/a&gt;, the forest was traversed by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; in their pursuit of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wanderer\"&gt;Dark Wanderer&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;following year&lt;/a&gt;, one of the shards of the destroyed &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; landed in the wood.\nIn the intervening years, the forest grew increasingly dangerous. A forgotten evil began returning to strength within the shadowed forest, ready to challenge those who might dare tread within. &lt;a href=\"Demon\"&gt;Demon&lt;/a&gt;s plagued the forest, including the &lt;a href=\"Fallen\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt;, which made their homes beneath the wood's darkest trees, namely those which were deeply affected by &lt;a href=\"Andariel\"&gt;Andariel&lt;/a&gt;'s foul &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;s. They established a village in the &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Grove\"&gt;Cursed Grove&lt;/a&gt;, located in the forest's south.\nThe rise of the &lt;a href=\"Bloodsworn\"&gt;Bloodsworn&lt;/a&gt; made the area far too dangerous for merchants to travel through, and &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; requested &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s clear them out so that the route might be used again. The Dark Wood was corrupted by the &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Rose\"&gt;Blood Rose&lt;/a&gt;, but the creature was slain at the hands of a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;adventurer/group of adventurers&lt;/a&gt;. The &lt;a href=\"Sisterhood%20of%20the%20Sightless%20Eye\"&gt;Sisterhood of the Sightless Eye&lt;/a&gt; later made efforts to cleanse the wood of corruption, starting with the &lt;a href=\"Fetid%20Swamp\"&gt;Fetid Swamp&lt;/a&gt;. They requested aid from adventurers in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; to aid them in this endeavor.\nWestmarch requested aid from adventurers. A large &lt;a href=\"Fallen\"&gt;Fallen&lt;/a&gt; tribe dwelled in the western side of the wood. Villagers in the area were travelling west in search of shelter, but could not pass through safely. They requested that adventurers clear the area of the Fallen, so that the roads would remain clear. &lt;a href=\"Gorja%20Caspan\"&gt;Gorja Caspan&lt;/a&gt; declared that the forest itself had to be cleared, given the corruption that had taken it.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nThe Dark Wood is a forested area in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", and can be reached by travelling through the &lt;a href=\"Underground%20Passage\"&gt;Underground Passage&lt;/a&gt; located in &lt;a href=\"Stony%20Field\"&gt;Stony Field&lt;/a&gt;. It is the home of the &lt;a href=\"Tree%20of%20Inifuss\"&gt;Tree of Inifuss&lt;/a&gt;, which the player will be required to find during the &lt;a href=\"Search%20for%20Cain\"&gt;Search for Cain&lt;/a&gt; quest.\nThe Dark Wood is inhabited by the same monster types found in previous areas of Act I, however, the Carver packs are noticeably larger than before. A Super Unique Brute named &lt;a href=\"Treehead%20Woodfist\"&gt;Treehead Woodfist&lt;/a&gt; can also be found here, near the Tree of Inifuss.\nA landmark that always appears in this area is the ruins of a large house, infested with numerous &lt;a href=\"Carver\"&gt;Carver&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Carver%20Shaman\"&gt;Carver Shaman&lt;/a&gt;s. The area has far more trees than any other area in Act I, with the foliage potentially obscuring foes. Two variants of Fallen camps are exclusive to this location.\nThe Dark Wood has one exit, leading into the &lt;a href=\"Black%20Marsh\"&gt;Black Marsh&lt;/a&gt;.\nDiablo Immortal.\nThe Dark Wood appears as a zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is a hub zone, and has a recommended &lt;a href=\"Character%20Level\"&gt;Character Level&lt;/a&gt; of 20-29. Originally, it was completed after &lt;a href=\"Ashwold%20Cemetery\"&gt;Ashwold Cemetery&lt;/a&gt;, but in the final version, players gain access to it after &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. "}
