{"id": "28583", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28583", "title": "Dataminer", "text": "Dataminer,\u00a0Unearths Spoils, is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Ghastly%20Gravedigger\"&gt;Ghastly Gravedigger&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Defiled%20Crypt\"&gt;Defiled Crypt&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He can only spawn in a fake crypt, as well as the one that has the &lt;a href=\"Jar%20of%20Souls\"&gt;Jar of Souls&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn combat, he has\u00a0Thunderstorm, Electrified and Jailer &lt;a href=\"Monster%20Traits%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;affixes&lt;/a&gt;.\nKilling him is required for the &lt;a href=\"Haunted\"&gt;Haunted&lt;/a&gt; achievement. A &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; to kill him may also be available in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt;, in which case the secondary objective is to kill 40 enemies."}
{"id": "43189", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43189", "title": "Daughters of Pain", "text": "The Daughters of Pain were the servants of &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;'s consort &lt;a href=\"Cydaea\"&gt;Cydaea&lt;/a&gt;, the Maiden of Lust. They were aligned with Azmodan's &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Army of Sin&lt;/a&gt;, defending the &lt;a href=\"Sin%20Heart\"&gt;Sin Hearts&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;Heart of the Damned&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20the%20Cursed\"&gt;Heart of the Cursed&lt;/a&gt; within the depths of the &lt;a href=\"Arreat%20Crater\"&gt;Arreat Crater&lt;/a&gt;. Many were slain by &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; during their quest to defeat Azmodan and break the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Siege of Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Siege%20of%20Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Siege of Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; was called there to rout the &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Army of Sin&lt;/a&gt; and kill &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;. Eventually, after making it passed &lt;a href=\"Bastion%27s%20Keep\"&gt;Bastion's Keep&lt;/a&gt; itself and into the &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Realm of Sin&lt;/a&gt;, the Nephalem was sent to destroy the &lt;a href=\"Sin%20Heart\"&gt;Sin Hearts&lt;/a&gt; before journeying to the &lt;a href=\"Heart%20of%20Sin%20%28Area%29\"&gt;Heart of Sin&lt;/a&gt; to slay Azmodan. The Daughters of Pain were summoned by Cydaea during her battles with the Nephalem to stop him from destroying the Sin Hearts and reaching her Lord's position. Many of them were slain while in battle with the mighty warrior, who eventually went on to kill their mistress and finally the Lord of Sin himself, ending the Siege of Bastion's Keep."}
