{"id": "37282", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37282", "title": "David Kim", "text": "David Kim (Kim Tae Hyun) is a former employee of &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20Entertainment\"&gt;Blizzard Entertainment&lt;/a&gt;. Kim was the lead systems designer for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\" from January 2017 until September 2020.\nBackground.\nKim joined Blizzard in October, 2007. After working on \"&lt;a href=\"StarCraft%20II\"&gt;StarCraft II&lt;/a&gt;\", he began working with &lt;a href=\"Team%203\"&gt;Team 3&lt;/a&gt; in January, 2017, as a lead systems designer for the \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20series\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" series. Before parting ways with Blizzard, Kim was the Principal Game Designer for \"&lt;a href=\"Warcraft\"&gt;World of Warcraft&lt;/a&gt;\". He is currently employed as a Lead Game Designer at Uncapped Games Studio of Tencent America."}
{"id": "37120", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37120", "title": "David L. Craddock", "text": "David L. Craddock is an author of various fiction and non-fiction works.\nBiography.\nCraddock played the beta of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Game%29\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;\" thanks to his uncle, who was aquainted with &lt;a href=\"Blizzard%20North\"&gt;Blizzard North&lt;/a&gt; staff members. \nCraddock started writing about games during college while doing a computer science major. In June 2000, he was flown to the Blizzard North office to meet members of staff. He ended up writing for Shack News, a gaming website. After leaving SN in 2007, he worked at IGN for a short time before entering into the freelance sector, writing for PlayStation: the Official Magazine, Electronic Arts, Good Old Games, Joystiq, Official Xbox magazine, and other companies. "}
