{"id": "21502", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=21502", "title": "Dawn", "text": "Dawn is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Hand%20Crossbows\"&gt;hand crossbow&lt;/a&gt; for the &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 50 to drop.\nPrior to 2.4, it had increased chances to &lt;a href=\"Stun\"&gt;Stun&lt;/a&gt; on hit.\nAs of 2.4, it gained a unique affix that, if used correctly, gives player a nearly permanent . With sufficient &lt;a href=\"cooldown\"&gt;cooldown&lt;/a&gt; reduction (about 36%), it actually allows Vengeance to recharge immediately after it expires."}
{"id": "42495", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=42495", "title": "Dawn of Damnation", "text": "Dawn of Damnation was an event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe invasion occurred in the year &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, when &lt;a href=\"Skarn\"&gt;Skarn&lt;/a&gt; led his &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic forces against &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;. They swept across &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;, before finally being halted at its &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;capital&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe event lasted two weeks, themed around the player(s) fighting against Skarn's forces. Players had to be at least &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;level&lt;/a&gt; 30 to take part. Heroes who met these criteria were prompted to accept a quest in Westmarch that kicked off this event. After assisting Westmarch's forces in expelling Skarn's demons, players were able to progress over the next couple of weeks through a series of daily missions (up to 42 missions per week) and event stages. \nCompleting missions could earn the player &lt;a href=\"Obol%20of%20the%20Damned\"&gt;obols of the damned&lt;/a&gt; that could be redeemed to acquire treasures including legendary crests and gems in the Event Shop. Additionally, all heroes could reap additional obols of the damned when certain server-wide milestones are reached.\nDevelopment.\nThe Dawn of Damnation was first introduced in the game's beta in December, 2021, to Korean and Japanese players."}
