{"id": "53273", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=53273", "title": "Death's Embrace", "text": "Death's Embrace is an exploration &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20V%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act V&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It is completed in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20Heights\"&gt;Westmarch Heights&lt;/a&gt;, where three Death Orbs are located in the streets. These orbs appear to be smaller versions of the &lt;a href=\"Soul%20Crucible\"&gt;Soul Crucible&lt;/a&gt;s from the Act V &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Mode\"&gt;campaign&lt;/a&gt;, but are destroyed by channeling on them uninterrupted rather than with damaging attacks.\nThese orbs are also guarded less heavily, albeit still significantly: In addition to any usual &lt;a href=\"reapers\"&gt;reapers&lt;/a&gt; infesting the Heights, a mix of Summoned &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20Archer\"&gt;Archers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20Soldier\"&gt;Soldiers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Summoned%20Shield%20Guard\"&gt;Shield Guards&lt;/a&gt; stands around each orb when first encountered, and a follow up wave of &lt;a href=\"Revenant\"&gt;Revenant&lt;/a&gt;s of a similar mix can spawn after the first guardians are killed.\nObjectives.\nLike other exploration bounties, the objectives will only be marked on the map once &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt; is a medium distance away from them; a significant portion of the Heights usually needs to be covered to find them all.\nA &lt;a href=\"Radiant%20Chest\"&gt;Radiant Chest&lt;/a&gt; appears where the last Death Orb is destroyed, in addition to the usual gold and experience."}
