{"id": "7093", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7093", "title": "Death's Web", "text": "Death's Web is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Unearthed%20Wand\"&gt;Unearthed Wand&lt;/a&gt; from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nAlthough at first, Death's Web may seem lackluster compared to the legions of skill bonuses that other unique &lt;a href=\"wands\"&gt;wands&lt;/a&gt; offer, Death's Web has the rarely-seen property of reducing enemy &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Resistance\"&gt;Poison Resistance&lt;/a&gt;. Therefore, Necromancers who specialize in &lt;a href=\"Poison%20Skills\"&gt;Poison Skills&lt;/a&gt; may find Death's Web a potent part of their arsenal.\nIt can also be highly useful for the &lt;a href=\"Rabies%20Werewolf\"&gt;Rabies Werewolf&lt;/a&gt;, purely due to its reduction to enemy poison resistance.\nAs a TC87 item, Death's Web is extremely rare, and can only be found in a handful of areas. \nStats.\nOne-Hand Damage: 22 To 28\nRequired Level: 66\nRequired Strength: 25\nDurability: 18\nStaff Class - "}
