{"id": "47564", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47564", "title": "Deathspeaker", "text": "The Deathspeaker is the head of the &lt;a href=\"Priests%20of%20Rathma\"&gt;Priests of Rathma&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nTo become deathspeaker, the aspiring &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt; had to travel to the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20the%20Deathspeaker\"&gt;Temple of the Deathspeaker&lt;/a&gt; and face deadly trials in order to prove their worth. Its halls are filled with the &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;corpse&lt;/a&gt;s of those who failed. An existing deathspeaker may appoint a successor while they are still alive. The deathspeaker has their own seal.\nHistory.\n&lt;a href=\"Kalan\"&gt;Kalan&lt;/a&gt; was the founder of the Priests of Rathma, and in so doing, served as the first deathspeaker. Kalan appointed &lt;a href=\"Daros\"&gt;Daros&lt;/a&gt; as his successor, who succeeded him. While initially an unpopular choice, Daros quickly proved his worth with the creation of the &lt;a href=\"Lidless%20Wall\"&gt;Lidless Wall&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt is unclear who succeeded Daros; &lt;a href=\"Mykan\"&gt;Mykan&lt;/a&gt;, however, is known to be one of the earliest deathspeakers of the order.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"End%20of%20Days\"&gt;End of Days&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Jurdann\"&gt;Jurdann&lt;/a&gt; was Deathspeaker, but was killed by the &lt;a href=\"Reapers\"&gt;Reapers&lt;/a&gt;. The spirit of &lt;a href=\"Ordan\"&gt;Ordan&lt;/a&gt; bid that his &lt;a href=\"Necromancer%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;former student&lt;/a&gt; take up the mantle of deathspeaker."}
