{"id": "48658", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48658", "title": "Deepstrider", "text": "s are a race of sea &lt;a href=\"animal\"&gt;creatures&lt;/a&gt; that roam the depths of &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;'s seas.\nLore.\nTentacled Deepstriders spend their lives rummaging in the brackish depths, where they can subsist on &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;carcasses&lt;/a&gt; for months. They have been recorded to grow to massive sizes, though in those cases it was because they were affected by powerful artifacts. In such cases, they were shown to be strong enough to shatter steel, and tear ships apart. There has also been a case of one being domesticated.\nIn-game.\nDifferent Deepstriders have been featured as &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt;es in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "44791", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44791", "title": "Deepstrider Behemoth", "text": "The is a monster seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is a major antagonist of the &lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt; extension.\nLore.\nTentacled &lt;a href=\"Deepstrider\"&gt;Deepstrider&lt;/a&gt;s spend their lives rummaging in the brackish depths, where they can subsist on &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;carcasses&lt;/a&gt; for months. This deepstrider runt's scavenging ended when it swallowed a chunk of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;. It burst into misshapen growth, which continued long after the stone was pulled free from its maw.\nAfter the &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231265\"&gt;destruction of the Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, a large shard crashed into the sea near &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt;. It came into possession of &lt;a href=\"the%20Warden%20%28Stormpoint%29\"&gt;the prison warden&lt;/a&gt;. Due to its corrupted nature, the whole &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Prison\"&gt;prison&lt;/a&gt; denizens were transformed to &lt;a href=\"Transformed%20%28monster%29\"&gt;hideous monsters&lt;/a&gt;. The warden was also transformed, but managed to keep his mind for a while.\nAs a result of loneliness, or perhaps the warped state of mind, the warden exposed the shard to a sea creature he befriended. Close proximity to &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;the shard&lt;/a&gt; mutated it over time into a behemoth. It swallowed the Worldstone shard.\nThe Deepstrider shared a close bond with the warden. When he was killed, it went on a rampage and captured a &lt;a href=\"Fern\"&gt;child&lt;/a&gt; who was present in the Warden's office. Both the &lt;a href=\"Esmund\"&gt;girl's brother&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; were in hot pursuit; with the brother diving into the sea to save her. While &lt;a href=\"Zatham\"&gt;another adventurer&lt;/a&gt; went to save the children, the Shard-seeker drew the behemoth's attention and fought it. The Deepstrider was ultimately slain.\nIn-game.\nThe Deepstrider Behemoth is a &lt;a href=\"boss\"&gt;boss&lt;/a&gt; in the \"&lt;a href=\"Terror%27s%20Tide\"&gt;Terror's Tide&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Bound%20for%20Eternity\"&gt;Bound for Eternity&lt;/a&gt;.\" It is fought in its &lt;a href=\"Deepstrider%20Lair\"&gt;lair&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "45076", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45076", "title": "Deepstrider Lair", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal%20quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; specific &lt;a href=\"zone\"&gt;zone&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\nThe Deepstrider Lair is a tidal cave that is located beneath the office of &lt;a href=\"the%20Warden%20%28Stormpoint%29\"&gt;the warden&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Abandoned%20Prison\"&gt;Abandoned Prison&lt;/a&gt;, and was home to the &lt;a href=\"Deepstrider%20Behemoth\"&gt;Deepstrider Behemoth&lt;/a&gt; before its death.\nIt is hinted that Woodruh regularly visited the cave, perhaps for leisure. One day, a shard of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; was swept into the cave. It was found by Woodruh, who mistook it for an ordinary rock and took it with himself.\nLater Woodruh (now mostly warped by the shard) befriended a sea creature that swam into the cave, and exposed the shard to it. This caused it to start mutating, and over time it grew into a behemoth. The Transformed behemoth made the cave its lair.\nAfter Woodruh was killed the behemoth went on a rampage and captured a &lt;a href=\"Fern\"&gt;child&lt;/a&gt; who was present in the Warden's office. This incurred the wrath of &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; who was also prese. With the aid of &lt;a href=\"another%20adventurer\"&gt;another adventurer&lt;/a&gt; they were able to kill the Deepstrider.\nIn-game.\nThe Deepstrider Lair zone is featured in the quest, &lt;a href=\"Bound%20for%20Eternity\"&gt;Bound for Eternity&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "44627", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44627", "title": "Defamer", "text": "s are members of the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\n are a type of &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt; seen in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". They are found in &lt;a href=\"Stormpoint\"&gt;Stormpoint&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ancients%27%20Cradle\"&gt;Ancients' Cradle&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tristram%20Cathedral%20%28Dungeon%29\"&gt;Tristram Cathedral&lt;/a&gt;."}
