{"id": "50557", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=50557", "title": "Defend the Vault", "text": "Defend the Vault is an event in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is exclusive to &lt;a href=\"Immortals\"&gt;Immortals&lt;/a&gt; players, and is their counterpart event to &lt;a href=\"Raid%20the%20Vault\"&gt;Raid the Vault&lt;/a&gt;. \nGameplay.\nImmortals may sign up at the entrance in the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Ascension\"&gt;Hall of Ascension&lt;/a&gt; to join the queue to defend. When a Shadow party raiding the Vault triggers an alarm (either by entering the 4th floor or failing to kill a Warden in time) the first Immortal party in the queue gets the chance to defend. However it may be possible for parties to get skipped depending on the power difference between the Shadow and Immortal parties. The Immortal party leader may also choose to automatically skip strong raids. When the alert comes up, the leader does not have to click on a button but all other party members must click accept. (This is an important distinction as for the party leader the \"cancel\" button is in the same place as \"accept\" for other party members, creating a chance to misclick).\nOnce Immortals enter the Vault, they must defeat the Shadows. This is the only aspect of gameplay on the Immortal side.\nRewards.\nIf the Immortals successfully defeat the Shadows, they get some items and &lt;a href=\"Hilts\"&gt;Hilts&lt;/a&gt; in varying quantity from 150 to 185. It is unconfirmed what the exact amount is based on but it is believed to be the Essentia stolen by the Shadows. The Hilts have a cap of 1400 per week. Furthermore the victorious Immortals also get prestige points that factor into ranking for &lt;a href=\"commendations\"&gt;commendations&lt;/a&gt;."}
