{"id": "43824", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43824", "title": "Defense of Cyrangar", "text": "Defense of Cyrangar (also called Castle Defense) is a game mode in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It is only accessible for players who have purged &lt;a href=\"Castle%20Cyrangar\"&gt;Castle Cyrangar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe event is themed around &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s trying to take the castle for their own, with the player's &lt;a href=\"warband\"&gt;warband&lt;/a&gt; defending their fortress. It can be played in two ways:\nNote that &lt;a href=\"ancestral%20weapons\"&gt;ancestral weapons&lt;/a&gt; have the highest drop rates in this event, matched only by &lt;a href=\"Purge%20the%20Depths\"&gt;Purge the Depths&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nOriginally only raids composed of the members of the same warband could enter Defense of Cyrangar. After the September 21 2023 update, this requirement was dropped and the event can be accessed from the NPC in Westmarch."}
{"id": "7722", "revid": "25338", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7722", "title": "Defense vs. Missile", "text": ""}
{"id": "7488", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=7488", "title": "Defense vs. Missiles", "text": "Defense vs. Missiles is a &lt;a href=\"special%20modifier\"&gt;special modifier&lt;/a&gt; found on some\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Unique%20Items\"&gt;Unique Items&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;Set Items&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Destruction\"&gt;Lord of Destruction&lt;/a&gt;, it adds a set amount to Defense against all ranged/projectile attacks, and stacks with the &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; skill &lt;a href=\"Avoid\"&gt;Avoid&lt;/a&gt;. It works against &lt;a href=\"arrows\"&gt;arrows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"bolts\"&gt;bolts&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Spikefiends\"&gt;quills&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"javelins\"&gt;javelins&lt;/a&gt;, and projectile elemental attacks. It does not work on damage over time spells like &lt;a href=\"Fire%20Wall%20%28monster%20skill%29\"&gt;Fire Wall&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Poison%20cloud\"&gt;Poison cloud&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", a similar concept is present in the form of &lt;a href=\"Damage%20Reduction\"&gt;reduced damage&lt;/a&gt; from ranged attacks, a secondary &lt;a href=\"Affix\"&gt;attribute&lt;/a&gt; that can occur randomly on several types of &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4852", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4852", "title": "Defensive Auras", "text": "Defensive Auras is the Second of the &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Skill%20Trees\"&gt;Skill Trees&lt;/a&gt;, and encompasses a number of skills, each with its own specific protective effect. As the name suggests, the skills contained therein are primarily defensive, though some have a healing/regenerating effect, such as &lt;a href=\"Meditation\"&gt;Meditation&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Prayer\"&gt;Prayer&lt;/a&gt;.\nFor the Paladin, the Defensive Auras are of great importance in multiplayer games because of their ability to protect/affect other party members. As with the &lt;a href=\"Offensive%20Auras\"&gt;Offensive Auras&lt;/a&gt;, the Defensive Auras are great in single-player, but really shine when they can be applied to a team.\nUsage Notes.\nThe only Defensive Aura that uses &lt;a href=\"mana\"&gt;mana&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href=\"Prayer\"&gt;Prayer&lt;/a&gt;, so don't worry about always having an Aura active, as any Aura is better than no Aura.\nA Paladin cannot use more than one Aura at the same time. Different Auras can be stacked by multiple Paladins.\nThe Act II &lt;a href=\"Desert%20Mercenary\"&gt;Desert Mercenary&lt;/a&gt; also uses Auras which may stack with a Paladin."}
{"id": "4055", "revid": "25014340", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4055", "title": "Defiance", "text": "Defiance is a &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Shielding himself and nearby companions within a glow of holy light, the Paladin guards himself to face the unjust in combat. By standing resolute and earnest in the face of opposition, his faith is his shield against harm.\"\nGeneral Information.\nDefiance is a popular Aura choice, due to its synergy to &lt;a href=\"Holy%20Shield\"&gt;Holy Shield&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Desert%20Mercenary\"&gt;Act II mercenaries&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0on Normal and Hell mode may possess this skill, giving other character classes access to this defensive aura.\nIt has no hidden bonuses, only a plain bonus to Defense, stacking to other similar effects. When inactive, it provides no benefit (aside from synergy).\nThe Rune word\u00a0\u00a0grants its user a permanent level 13-16 Defiance aura as long as it is equipped.\u00a0"}
{"id": "16502", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16502", "title": "Defiance (magic suffix)", "text": "Defiance is a &lt;a href=\"suffix\"&gt;suffix&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;. It provides a reduction to poison length caused by &lt;a href=\"poison\"&gt;poison&lt;/a&gt; attacks.\nIt doesn't start spawning on items until &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; 25.\nPoison Length Reduction reduces the amount of Poison damage taken.\nStats.\n\"Can appear on:\" &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;\n\"Is available on:\" &lt;a href=\"Amulets\"&gt;Amulets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Body%20Armor\"&gt;Body Armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Circlets\"&gt;Circlets&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Shields\"&gt;Shields&lt;/a&gt;"}
