{"id": "17131", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17131", "title": "Defiled Crypt", "text": "The Defiled Crypt is the name of three dungeons in the &lt;a href=\"Cemetery%20of%20the%20Forsaken\"&gt;Cemetery of the Forsaken&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20I%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act I&lt;/a&gt; of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". All three can be explored, but two are \"false\", as only the \"true\" crypt holds the crown of &lt;a href=\"King%20Leoric\"&gt;King Leoric&lt;/a&gt; within the &lt;a href=\"Chancellor%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Chancellor's Tomb&lt;/a&gt; that makes up its third level. The second level is very small, serving as a fight area for &lt;a href=\"Manglemaw\"&gt;Manglemaw&lt;/a&gt;, who guards access to the tomb. The false crypts only have one level.\nThe entrances to all the crypts are randomized between four possible doorways in the Cemetery. There is no way to tell which is false aside from exploring them, unless a &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; has been offered to complete an event or kill a monster in one of the crypts, in which case that entrance will be marked on the map.\nIn every game, one of the two false crypts will be medium sized and contain either the &lt;a href=\"Jar%20of%20Souls\"&gt;Jar of Souls&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"The%20Matriarch%27s%20Bones\"&gt;The Matriarch's Bones&lt;/a&gt; event. &lt;a href=\"Dataminer\"&gt;Dataminer&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt; monster, sometimes appears there as well. The other false crypt will be small, but occasionally the unique &lt;a href=\"Digger%20O%27Dell\"&gt;Digger O'Dell&lt;/a&gt;, a &lt;a href=\"Resplendent%20Chest\"&gt;Resplendent Chest&lt;/a&gt;, or the &lt;a href=\"Cursed%20Chest\"&gt;Cursed Chest&lt;/a&gt; of the Plunderers can be found inside. The \"true\" crypt sometimes houses Uniques &lt;a href=\"John%20Gorham%20Coffin\"&gt;John Gorham Coffin&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Drury%20Brown\"&gt;Drury Brown&lt;/a&gt;, in addition to &lt;a href=\"Manglemaw\"&gt;Manglemaw&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrivia.\nThe \"true and false\" instances of the Defiled Crypt follow a pattern shared by the &lt;a href=\"Passage%20to%20Corvus\"&gt;Passage to Corvus&lt;/a&gt; later in the game (which has 3 false instances), and &lt;a href=\"Tal%20Rasha%27s%20Tomb\"&gt;Tal Rasha's Tomb&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" (which has 6). In those cases a mechanism is available to determine the true instance before entering it."}
