{"id": "31126", "revid": "21257", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31126", "title": "Delsere", "text": "Delsere was a student at the &lt;a href=\"Yshari%20Sanctum\"&gt;Yshari Sanctum&lt;/a&gt;. A skilled artisan, he took his quest for perfection in his works to the extreme.\nBiography.\nLike many of his fellow students, Delsere was fascinated by &lt;a href=\"Li-Ming\"&gt;Li-Ming&lt;/a&gt;, another student at the sanctum. He swore that he would create a &lt;a href=\"Delsere%27s%20Magnum%20Opus\"&gt;master work&lt;/a&gt; of armor for her, and that she would one day wear it. However, his quest for perfection went to levels of excess. When he showed &lt;a href=\"Fierce%20Gauntlets\"&gt;gauntlets&lt;/a&gt; to Master &lt;a href=\"Valthek\"&gt;Valthek&lt;/a&gt;, he asked how they made the teacher feel. When Valthek explained that he did not understand the question, Delsere stormed off. For his &lt;a href=\"Harness%20of%20Truth\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, he described it as resplendant. When asked why that mattered, he ranted that \"form is function,\" and any praise for his &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;al crafting abilities only infuriated him more. Even the &lt;a href=\"Leg%20Guards%20of%20Mystery\"&gt;leg guards&lt;/a&gt; were crafted repeatedly, with only minimal increase to their magical properties. When Valthek pointed this out, Delsere called him a \"visionless cretin\".\nFinally, Delsere reached the last stage of his magnum opus: a &lt;a href=\"Shrouded%20Mask\"&gt;mask&lt;/a&gt; that he declared would be the jewel of his work. Not long after making such a declaration, however, he broke down, weeping that he had to start over. Delsere disappeared soon afterwards, along with his armor set. Valthek reflected that his madness and departure was a tragic loss. Delsere had melted down so many pieces of armor in his work, calling them inelegant. Yet even these had been more beautiful than one most artisans could hope to create.\nIn-game.\nDelsere is referenced in the &lt;a href=\"Delsere%27s%20Magnum%20Opus\"&gt;Delsere's Magnum Opus&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"item%20set\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"The%20Shame%20of%20Delsere\"&gt;The Shame of Delsere&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"belt\"&gt;belt&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "30613", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=30613", "title": "Delsere's Magnum Opus", "text": "Delsere's Magnum Opus is a 6 piece class &lt;a href=\"item%20set\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt; for s for level 70, focused on constant use of &lt;a href=\"Slow%20Time\"&gt;Slow Time&lt;/a&gt;. This set can only drop at &lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; difficulty. It was added in patch 2.2.0.\nAll set pieces are restricted to Wizards only. Even\u00a0&lt;a href=\"transmogrification\"&gt;transmogrification&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0of these items is only available to Wizard class.\nPieces.\nThe set consists of six pieces. All six are required to complete the set, and all of them are Wizard-restricted.\nSet Bonus.\nThe first bonus creates Slow Time bubbles with most secondary projectiles of the listed skills, such as Arcane Torrent's Static Discharge shocks and Arcane Orb's Frozen Orb shards. Slow Time does not need to be in the player's action bar.\nThe Teleport cooldown reset happens the moment the Wizard enters a Slow Time and remains in effect constantly; they may cast Teleport as fast as their cast speed allows while inside bubbles. Teleporting from inside to outside the bubble has a normal cooldown.\nThe second and third bonuses work with the &lt;a href=\"Archon\"&gt;Archon&lt;/a&gt; version of Slow Time, although considering the nature of the third bonus, it is pointless to use this set in tandem with Archon.\nThe third bonus effect is multiplicative, and applies to any enemies even partially touched by at least one Slow Time sphere, even if they are immune to &lt;a href=\"Crowd%20Control\"&gt;Crowd Control&lt;/a&gt;.\nSynergies.\nFor extra effect, one may combine this set with &lt;a href=\"Crown%20of%20the%20Primus\"&gt;Crown of the Primus&lt;/a&gt;. If Slow Time is in player's action bar, the Crown will cause a Slow Time bubble to follow the player (no casting required), and the player can still cast Slow Time manually and cause them with the set 2-piece bonus; these latter bubbles do not move. The bubble that follows the player does not provide the 2-piece Teleport bonus, but works with all the others.\nAlso helpful are items that empower the other skills affected by this set, such as &lt;a href=\"The%20Twisted%20Sword\"&gt;The Twisted Sword&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Unstable%20Scepter\"&gt;Unstable Scepter&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Gesture%20of%20Orpheus\"&gt;Gesture of Orpheus&lt;/a&gt; is generally not useful with the updated version of this set, since active casting of Slow Time is done rarely or not at all.\nBugs.\nA quirk occurs when &lt;a href=\"Teleport%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Teleport&lt;/a&gt;'s Wormhole rune is used, which normally allows a second Teleport within 3 seconds before its cooldown activates. The 3 second period is \"not\" reset by being in a bubble, so exiting a Slow Time bubble within 3 seconds of Teleporting into or within it causes Teleport to go on cooldown 3 seconds after the cast. This may be a bug, since this occurs even if the Teleport into the bubble is the second cast of the Wormhole pattern, in which case it would've gone on cooldown immediately, and therefore should be reset.\nSome players have reported Slow Time not always activating when enemies are hit with the appropriate skills.\nPrevious Set Bonus.\nThis set formerly required active casting of &lt;a href=\"Slow%20Time\"&gt;Slow Time&lt;/a&gt;, worked with slightly different abilities, and was tuned differently:\nThe first bonus triggered even if the skills did not hit an enemy."}
