{"id": "52178", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52178", "title": "Demon Summoner", "text": "A Demon Summoner is a monstrous &lt;a href=\"Objects\"&gt;object&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". In &lt;a href=\"Campaign%20Mode\"&gt;Campaign Mode&lt;/a&gt; they are found within &lt;a href=\"Arreat%20Crater\"&gt;Arreat Crater&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20III%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act III&lt;/a&gt;, while in &lt;a href=\"Adventure%20Mode\"&gt;Adventure Mode&lt;/a&gt; they appear in the equivalent part of &lt;a href=\"Upper%20Realm%20of%20Infernal%20Fate\"&gt;Upper Realm of Infernal Fate&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Act%20IV%20%28Diablo%20III%29\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt;. They are usually arranged in groups of three or four around demonic circles, presumably used to summon demons. In the Crater, they do not continuously summon demons once the surrounding ones have been cleared away, nor do they attack, but they can still be destroyed with combat damage like any monster.\nPhysically, they are large jagged triangular totems with long curving spikes sticking out, composed of upper and a lower pyramidal parts sandwiching glowing demonic energy. They appear to be constructed of metal, bone and even sharp teeth. They hover above the ground, falling down into separate pieces once destroyed.\nDemon Summoners are very similar to the Demon Gates used by &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt; in his boss fight. &lt;a href=\"The%20Demon%20Gates\"&gt;The Demon Gates&lt;/a&gt; exploration &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; also includes a variation appearing in Arreat Crater just like in Campaign Mode, but scattered throughout the zone and noticeably spewing out demons upon approach."}
