{"id": "26412", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26412", "title": "Demon Trooper", "text": "Demon Troopers (a.k.a. Demon Raiders or Demon Marauders) are a type of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic warrior.\nIn-game.\nDiablo Immortal.\n&lt;a href=\"Demon%20Assault%20Trooper\"&gt;Demon Assault Trooper&lt;/a&gt;s are encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Destruction%27s%20End\"&gt;Destruction's End&lt;/a&gt;\" in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDiablo III.\nDemon Troopers are the most common &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; enemies in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", the major bulk, backbone and cannon fodder of &lt;a href=\"Azmodan\"&gt;Azmodan&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Army%20of%20Sin\"&gt;Army of Sin&lt;/a&gt;. In , they are replaced by &lt;a href=\"Warscarred%20Marauder\"&gt;Warscarred Marauder&lt;/a&gt;s with the same characteristics.\nVisually, they are very similar, but not entirely identical, to &lt;a href=\"Crater%20Assault%20Troops\"&gt;Crater Assault Troops&lt;/a&gt;.\nDemon Troopers are always encountered in large numbers, but do not pose any danger. They are average in terms of speed, toughness and strength, and are easily killed by any area attacks, despite their hulking appearance and armor. They can, however, climb walls (and therefore arrive unexpectedly), or pour through the maws of &lt;a href=\"Demonic%20Hell%20Bearer\"&gt;Demonic Hell Bearer&lt;/a&gt;s.\nDuring fights with Azmodan and the &lt;a href=\"Siegebreaker\"&gt;Siegebreaker&lt;/a&gt;, a large number of Demon Troopers will support them, arriving endlessly, but their tide can be halted by destroying the sources of their reinforcements.\nIn the &lt;a href=\"Treasure%20Realm\"&gt;Treasure Realm&lt;/a&gt;, a variant of Demon Troopers called &lt;a href=\"Treasure%20Realm%20Sentry\"&gt;Sentries&lt;/a&gt; can be found.\nDevelopment.\nConcept art for Diablo III depicts Act III demons titled \"Crater Assault Troops.\" Visually, they bear great resemblance to Demon Warriors, and are possibly an early concept for them.\nHeroes of the Storm.\nDemon Troopers can be summoned by Azmodan in \"&lt;a href=\"Heroes%20of%20the%20Storm\"&gt;Heroes of the Storm&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
