{"id": "40114", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=40114", "title": "Demon Wolf (Cut)", "text": "Demon Wolf is an cut monster type, nothing is known about it apart of it being an demonic wolf that would appear most likely in Act I,III. Has graphics at token WO that can be used in the game.\nIn the monster planning sheet of Act I, they are referred as \"Evil Wolves\" and were supposed to attack the same target in packs, fleeing easily if encountering retaliation.\nIt needs extensive work to be a working monster. It doesn't have a Corpse graphic, but the last frame of Defeated animation can be made into it. It's attack animation is unfinished, but it's special \"spell\" animation can be used as an attack. It has invisible frames that need to be cut in it's animations so they don't become invisible. Animdata.d2 needs new entries of Demon Wolf to be added with an information to tell the game what frame of Attack Animation it damages you. Then an entry in monstats.txt with AI (&lt;a href=\"The%20Smith\"&gt;Smith&lt;/a&gt; AI works), Sounds and Statistics."}
