{"id": "43724", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=43724", "title": "Momentary Lapses", "text": "Momentary Lapses is a &lt;a href=\"Realm%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Realm of Damnation&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"side%20quest\"&gt;side quest&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It triggers if the player frees &lt;a href=\"Padius\"&gt;Padius&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic vines whenever he appears to the south of the &lt;a href=\"Forest%20of%20Misery\"&gt;Forest of Misery&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"waypoint\"&gt;waypoint&lt;/a&gt; in the Forest of Misery.\nDescription.\n\"The &lt;a href=\"angel\"&gt;angel&lt;/a&gt; Padius was trapped by vines within the Forest of Misery. Talk with him.\"\n\"Padius is heading deeper into the forest to search for his abducted comrades. Follow him.\"\n\"You've found an angel robbed of its &lt;a href=\"light\"&gt;light&lt;/a&gt; by vines. Check the body, but keep Padius back so he does not suffer the same fate.\"\n\"Padius is unwilling to leave without following the path of the feeding vines. Escort him.\"\n\"You've found what appears to be the angel &lt;a href=\"Muqiel\"&gt;Muqiel&lt;/a&gt; trapped in vines with a pile of other angelic \"bodies.\" Cut the vines that bind them.\"\n\"Muqiel vanished when you attempted to help, and a &lt;a href=\"Gleameater\"&gt;massive demonic creature&lt;/a&gt; attempted to capture Padius. Kill it.\"\n\"Search the bodies for Muqiel. Maybe they still live.\"\n\"With the creature dead, images of the angelic bodies and Muqiel have disappeared before your eyes. Talk to Padius.\""}
{"id": "24850", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24850", "title": "Momentum", "text": "Momentum\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Monk\"&gt;Monk&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0passive skill, unlocked at level 66.\nIn-game.\nThis effect does not stack, but works regardless of which method the Monk uses to move: running with &lt;a href=\"Tempest%20Rush\"&gt;Tempest Rush&lt;/a&gt;, dashing with &lt;a href=\"Dashing%20Strike\"&gt;Dashing Strike&lt;/a&gt; and teleporting with &lt;a href=\"Fists%20of%20Thunder\"&gt;Fists of Thunder&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Epiphany\"&gt;Epiphany&lt;/a&gt; count as well (if the Monk covers the required distance). Even being pulled by a monster's Vortex affix or being a victim of a &lt;a href=\"Knockback\"&gt;Knockback&lt;/a&gt; will suffice. Once 25 yards are crossed, the count is reset, so the Monk must move another 25 yards without stopping to refresh it.\nThis buff is not multiplicative with other damage modifiers."}
{"id": "44236", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44236", "title": "Momentum's Flow", "text": " is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary\"&gt;Legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"pants\"&gt;pants&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". It enables the player to use a variant of &lt;a href=\"Flying%20Kick\"&gt;Flying Kick&lt;/a&gt;.\n bears cosmetic synergy with &lt;a href=\"Tranquility%27s%20Gaze\"&gt;Tranquility's Gaze&lt;/a&gt; (head), &lt;a href=\"Rising%20Tide\"&gt;Rising Tide&lt;/a&gt; (shoulders), &lt;a href=\"Breath%20of%20Incense\"&gt;Breath of Incense&lt;/a&gt; (chest), &lt;a href=\"Dragon%27s%20Indignation\"&gt;Dragon's Indignation&lt;/a&gt; (main hand), and &lt;a href=\"Reaching%20Rebuke\"&gt;Reaching Rebuke&lt;/a&gt; (off hand)."}
{"id": "38863", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38863", "title": "Momentum (Diablo IV)", "text": "Momentum is a passive talent in the Berserker (Orange) tree.\nIn-game.\nApplies to all damaging skills and basic attacks, and Fury can be generated regardless of whether the original skill generated Fury or spent it.\nThe amount (and only the amount) grows non-linearly with extra points (each additional point adds less Fury).\nThe chance does not change and scales with &lt;a href=\"Proc%20Coefficient\"&gt;Proc Coefficient&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "4975", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4975", "title": "Monarch", "text": "Monarchs are the &lt;a href=\"Elite%20Items\"&gt;elite&lt;/a&gt; versions of s. \nIt is popular for being the shield that gets four possible sockets at the lowest Strength requirement (not counting Paladin-specific shields). It is therefore the easiest shield for assembling complex four-&lt;a href=\"Rune\"&gt;Rune&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Words\"&gt;Rune Words&lt;/a&gt;. It is also the only non-class specific shield to have up to four sockets and have the lowest weight designation.\nStats.\nDefense: 133-148\nLevel Requirement: 54\nStrength Requirement: 156\nChance to Block: (&lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;) / (&lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt;, ) / (&lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Necromancer\"&gt;Necromancer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Sorceress\"&gt;Sorceress&lt;/a&gt;)\nDurability: 86\nSockets: 4\n&lt;a href=\"Smite\"&gt;Smite&lt;/a&gt; Damage: 12-34\nType: Light\nQuality Level: 72"}
