{"id": "28446", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28446", "title": "Monstrous Dune Thresher", "text": "Monstrous Dune Thresher, Bane of the Dunes,\u00a0is a\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Sand%20Shark\"&gt;Sand Shark&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0that spawns for an unmarked event in the\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Stinging%20Winds\"&gt;Stinging Winds&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0in\u00a0\"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\u00a0\nPlayers may find a pool of quicksand with the peasant with his legs bitten off in the middle. When players approach, Monstrous Dune Thresher drags the screaming peasant underground, emerging afterwards.\nIt has Extra Health and Electrified affixes, and in addition, has much higher damage than other unique Sand Sharks. However, while unburrowed, it moves and attacks much slower than any other Dune Thresher. Visually, it is the largest Sand Shark in game."}
{"id": "48812", "revid": "2011810", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=48812", "title": "Monstrous Essence", "text": "Monstrous Essence is an item in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nGameplay.\nMonstrous Essence is randomly dropped by &lt;a href=\"monsters\"&gt;monsters&lt;/a&gt; in the overworld, &lt;a href=\"Hidden%20Lair\"&gt;Hidden Lair&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Abyssal%20Verge\"&gt;Abyssal Verge&lt;/a&gt; and chests in &lt;a href=\"Erebban\"&gt;Erebban&lt;/a&gt;.\nA player can only carry 10 Monstrous Essence, at which point they must be turned in at one of the Horardric Altars found in most towns.\nOnce turned in, the player is rewarded with some gold and items (including a chance for a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;Legendary Item&lt;/a&gt;), and a chance to reveal a new page in the &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Bestiary\"&gt;Horadric Bestiary&lt;/a&gt;. After 3 turn ins on a particular day, the rewards are reduced and no more pages can be revealed."}
{"id": "37430", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=37430", "title": "Montaht", "text": ""}
{"id": "5520", "revid": "865253", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5520", "title": "Moo Moo Farm", "text": ""}
{"id": "47973", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=47973", "title": "Moon", "text": "The Moon is &lt;a href=\"Sanctuary\"&gt;Sanctuary&lt;/a&gt;'s natural satellite.\nLore.\nThe Moon has lunar phases, and sometimes moves in front of the &lt;a href=\"sun\"&gt;sun&lt;/a&gt;, forming an eclipse. This includes &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lunar_eclipse%23Blood_moon\"&gt;Blood moons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blue_moon\"&gt;Blue moons&lt;/a&gt;. The nights preceding the full moon are sometimes far more dangerous than the event itself.\nThe moon's light is said to be &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;al; the &lt;a href=\"Celestial%20Court\"&gt;Celestial Court&lt;/a&gt; utilizes a form of ancient magic that is enhanced by the moon and stars. Drawing power from the moon can grant one the power to obscure or transform or control, depending on its phase.\nSharval Mythology.\nThe moon, most particularly its lunar phases, played a key role in the beliefs of the &lt;a href=\"Witch%20Circles\"&gt;Witch Circles&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Sharval%20Wilds\"&gt;Sharval Wilds&lt;/a&gt;. They believed that the moon gave equal favor to all who sought it, renewing its strength as it turned its face (went through lunar phases). Their beliefs held that the moon was at its weakest when it \"hid its face\" (a new moon), but always renewed itself. They believed that the moon was like a child, that it hid its face at times, showed it clearly during others. They believed none of the moon's faces were weak, only waiting. They could draw on the power of the moon for their wards, but to draw upon the moon overmuch was to overwhelm it. As such, all the circles knew to exercise caution when drawing on the moon's power. They believed that the moon's interests changed, and as such, the power they drew from it shifted in kind.\nOther Mythologies.\nAccording to &lt;a href=\"Covetous%20Shen\"&gt;Covetous Shen&lt;/a&gt;, Sanctuary originally had two moons. &lt;a href=\"Liria\"&gt;Liria&lt;/a&gt; was the personification of the second moon. \nThe moon plays a role in &lt;a href=\"Druid\"&gt;Druid&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"divination\"&gt;divination&lt;/a&gt; practices. Under the stars and new moon, devotees often see new patterns in the night sky, hinting at things yet to come.\nThe blood moon persists as a sign of woe for the most superstitious &lt;a href=\"Zakarum\"&gt;Zakarum&lt;/a&gt; faithful. Children born under it are often considered cursed and cast out, lest it spread.\n&lt;a href=\"Lunar%20Awakening\"&gt;Lunar Awakening&lt;/a&gt; is apparently tied to the moon."}
{"id": "3306", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3306", "title": "Moon Clan", "text": "The Moon Clan are a &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; clan.\nLore.\nThe Moon Clan have presence in &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ivgorod%20%28Country%29\"&gt;Ivgorod&lt;/a&gt;. The skin of these khazra has a pale, luminous glow. It is said that the Moon Clan once herded &lt;a href=\"Hellhound\"&gt;Hellhound&lt;/a&gt;s, as their immunity to &lt;a href=\"lightning\"&gt;lightning&lt;/a&gt; made them impervious to the beasts' electrical discharges.\nShortly before &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, Moon Clan khazra on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; were cowed into the service of &lt;a href=\"Dravec\"&gt;Dravec&lt;/a&gt;, who was empowered by the &lt;a href=\"Lord%20of%20Damnation\"&gt;Lord of Damnation&lt;/a&gt;. By 1270, they attacked &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%27s%20Watch\"&gt;Sentinel's Watch&lt;/a&gt;. They also expanded their encampment, and razed &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Razed%20Village\"&gt;villages&lt;/a&gt;, using the villagers as sacrifice in order to summon &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Clan\"&gt;Blood Clan&lt;/a&gt; khazra as reinforcement. &lt;a href=\"Westmarch\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt; offered &lt;a href=\"bounties\"&gt;bounties&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s to clear out the khazra.\nIn &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231285\"&gt;1285&lt;/a&gt;, the clan was temporarily enslaved by &lt;a href=\"Urik%20the%20Seer\"&gt;Urik the Seer&lt;/a&gt;. His &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; awakened a bloodlust in the khazra, and they flocked to him in hordes. A few managed to escape (those who understood what Urik was doing), but they were insignificant. However, Urik was killed shortly after by &lt;a href=\"the%20Nephalem\"&gt;the Nephalem&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nMoon Clan khazra are encountered in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", in each case representing baseline khazra. In \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", they are a common enemy seen in the &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt; zone. Despite what their lore would suggest, they bear no particular resistance to lightning attacks."}
{"id": "46888", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=46888", "title": "Moon Clan Encampment", "text": "The is the main settlement of the &lt;a href=\"Moon%20Clan\"&gt;Moon Clan&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"khazra\"&gt;khazra&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Zavain\"&gt;Mount Zavain&lt;/a&gt;. It is located to the north of &lt;a href=\"Sentinel%27s%20Watch\"&gt;Sentinel's Watch&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nThe is a Mount Zavain zone in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
