{"id": "20327", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=20327", "title": "Moonlight Ward", "text": "The Moonlight Ward is a &lt;a href=\"Legendary%20Items\"&gt;legendary&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"amulets\"&gt;amulet&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". It requires &lt;a href=\"character%20level\"&gt;character level&lt;/a&gt; 8 to drop.\nThis amulet is mostly known for the highest possible &lt;a href=\"Arcane\"&gt;Arcane&lt;/a&gt; damage bonus in game: (5% higher than any normal amulet). In return, it leaves very little space for variation, often making players sacrifice the &lt;a href=\"Attack%20Speed\"&gt;Attack Speed&lt;/a&gt; affix if they want an additional Core stat or &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0Damage roll.\nThe unique affix summons arcane stars orbiting the character with each successful attack against nearby enemy, and can hold up to 4 at once. Whenever an enemy comes \"very\" close to the Wizard (7.5 yards or less), one of the stars will detonate, centering the blast at the victim. There is a small (about 0.5 seconds) cooldown on how often the spheres may explode. The effect is very similar to &lt;a href=\"Arcane%20Orb\"&gt;Arcane Orb&lt;/a&gt; with Arcane Orbit rune, but is classified as a different skill and therefore is not affected by damage increases to Arcane Orb."}
