{"id": "45565", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45565", "title": "Morwith", "text": "Morwith is a sea &lt;a href=\"witch\"&gt;witch&lt;/a&gt; that terrorized the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Sea\"&gt;Forgotten Sea&lt;/a&gt; for years with her &lt;a href=\"Drowned\"&gt;Drowned&lt;/a&gt; force of &lt;a href=\"Dread%20Reavers\"&gt;reavers&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nMorwith was originally one of the elders of the &lt;a href=\"Lilin\"&gt;Lilin&lt;/a&gt;, and the eldest among them who advocated leaving &lt;a href=\"Ancients%27%20Cradle\"&gt;Ancients' Cradle&lt;/a&gt;. Morwith was rebuked for her position, but not stripped of her title. Tired of the oppression and hypocrisy of the &lt;a href=\"Inari\"&gt;Inari&lt;/a&gt;, she stole the &lt;a href=\"Pathstone\"&gt;Pathstone&lt;/a&gt; and fled from the Cradle with her followers amongst the Lilin. The heist was carried out in a single night.\nHer group were pursued by an army of Inari, who wanted to retrieve the relic. A great naval battle was fought over the Pathstone, with Morwith's group eventually falling under a hail of arrows. The battle was ended by &lt;a href=\"Haffegul\"&gt;a deepstrider&lt;/a&gt;, who decimated the survivors of both sides. Injured, Morwith was washed ashore a desolate island. In madness born from grief or obsession, Morwith used the Pathstone to cloud the sea and resurrect her tribesmen as &lt;a href=\"Drowned\"&gt;waterlogged undead&lt;/a&gt;.\nSince then, she and her band of &lt;a href=\"Dread%20Reaver\"&gt;Dread Reaver&lt;/a&gt;s terrorized the &lt;a href=\"Forgotten%20Sea\"&gt;Forgotten Sea&lt;/a&gt;.\nTrail of Terror.\nAs &lt;a href=\"the%20Shard-seeker\"&gt;the Shard-seeker&lt;/a&gt; pursued the &lt;a href=\"Cult%20of%20Terror\"&gt;Cult of Terror&lt;/a&gt;, they discovered that the cult sought to purify the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt; shard of &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;'s taint before delivering it to &lt;a href=\"Diablo\"&gt;Diablo&lt;/a&gt;. They also discovered a map with an island in the Forgotten Sea marked out. &lt;a href=\"Zatham\"&gt;Zatham&lt;/a&gt; recognized it as the &lt;a href=\"Ancients%27%20Cradle\"&gt;Ancients' Cradle&lt;/a&gt;, and announcesd that it could only be reached with the help of the Pathstone, which was in the possession of Morwith.\nDread Reaver.\nTogether with some sailors, the Shard-seeker and Zatham set sail aboard the latter's boat on the Forgotten Sea. \nThis attracted Morwith's attention, and she attacked them with her band of drowned reavers. At the end, Morwith was murdered by Zatham in a moment of inattention.\nIn-game.\nMorwith appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". Though she is the main antagonist of the &lt;a href=\"Dread%20Reaver\"&gt;Dread Reaver&lt;/a&gt; dungeon, she's not fought as a boss, as Zatham assassinates her before this can happen."}
{"id": "45013", "revid": "1687225", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45013", "title": "Mosaic Rune Word", "text": "Mosaic is the &lt;a href=\"Rune%20Word\"&gt;rune word&lt;/a&gt; \" for &lt;a href=\"katars\"&gt;katars&lt;/a&gt; in \"\". It is &lt;a href=\"Ladder\"&gt;Ladder&lt;/a&gt; only.\nMosaic is a moderately expensive rune word to make, requiring a &lt;a href=\"Gul%20Rune\"&gt;Gul Rune&lt;/a&gt; and a &lt;a href=\"Mal%20Rune\"&gt;Mal Rune&lt;/a&gt;. The rewards are great, however, as &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Talon%20Kicksin\"&gt;Kicksins&lt;/a&gt; benefit massively from the chance of not consuming charges, essentially allowing them to proc any charged attacks once for every kick. Two Mosaics can be wielded at a time to guarantee that charges are never used. The Mosaic runeword arguably renders all other claws obsolete for martial arts assassins for these reasons, though &lt;a href=\"Trap%20Assassin\"&gt;Trapsins&lt;/a&gt; have better alternative options.\nIn addition to working extremely well with &lt;a href=\"Dragon%20Talon\"&gt;Dragon Talon&lt;/a&gt;, Mosaic is very powerful with elemental Assassin attacks, such as &lt;a href=\"Phoenix%20Strike\"&gt;Phoenix Strike&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Claws%20of%20Thunder\"&gt;Claws of Thunder&lt;/a&gt;. Therefore, claws with &lt;a href=\"staffmod\"&gt;staffmod&lt;/a&gt;s for such skills are highly sought after on Ladder. \nResult:\nRune Effects:\nRune Word Bonuses:"}
