{"id": "38480", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=38480", "title": "Mounts", "text": "Mounts are a new feature in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\", added for the very first time in the &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20%28Series%29\"&gt;\"Diablo\" series&lt;/a&gt;.\nIn-game.\nMounts are unlocked through the game's primary questline, specifically upon reaching &lt;a href=\"Act%20IV%20%28Diablo%20IV%29\"&gt;Act IV&lt;/a&gt; and completing the &lt;a href=\"Diablo_IV_Quests\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; . They are used as a means of transportation for traversing across long distances in the open world to quicker reach one's targets. The mount's speed is variable depending on cursor distance, and three charges that make the horse sprint for a short distance. Dismounting puts it on a 10 second-cooldown.\nWhile mounted, the character's aggro range is greatly decreased, meaning that &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s will not attack on sight, only if the player approaches them. While mounted, a \"fear gauge\" is displayed on the horseriding's UI; monster attacks will fill the gauge, and if completed, the player is forced to dismount. If this happens, the mount is then put on a 30-second cooldown. \nMounts can be customized via their &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, saddle, and can have trophies dangling from them (said trophies including severed heads). Mount trophies can be attached to the saddle or the mount's flank. Different types of mounts exist, including &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic horses, flayed horses, and &lt;a href=\"undead\"&gt;undead&lt;/a&gt; horses. Mounts can be obtained in a variety of ways, such as by completing puzzles, finding hidden locations, slaying certain monsters, or completing certain &lt;a href=\"quests\"&gt;quests&lt;/a&gt;. Once a mount and customizations are unlocked, they can be used in all game modes for any and all characters that the player creates. All horse variations, as well as armor, and trophy customization, are aesthetic only, and do not change the way that players play in any way.\nAll character &lt;a href=\"classes\"&gt;classes&lt;/a&gt; have special dismounting attacks that allow them to perform a special offensive action the very moment they leap off their mounts. Players can collect &lt;a href=\"herbs\"&gt;herbs&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"ores\"&gt;ores&lt;/a&gt;, and other &lt;a href=\"items\"&gt;items&lt;/a&gt; while mounted.\nDevelopment.\nThe developers decided against jousting or fighting from horseback, as it did not feel true to the series. Furthermore, the mount's speed across terrain was supposed to be altered by collecting different types of horseshoes, and hoof plates."}
{"id": "29514", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29514", "title": "Mounty Burns", "text": "Mounty Burns, Etherweigh,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Vault%20Sentry\"&gt;Vault Sentry&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Vault\"&gt;The Vault&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn combat, he has Reflects Damage and Electrified affixes."}
{"id": "26697", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=26697", "title": "Mourdred", "text": "Mourdred, Beast of the Cave,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;unique&lt;/a&gt;\u00a0&lt;a href=\"Maggot%20Brood\"&gt;Maggot Brood&lt;/a&gt; that can be found in &lt;a href=\"Perilous%20Cave\"&gt;Perilous Cave&lt;/a&gt; Level 1 in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nMourdred can be found in the location where several dead Maggot Broods and are lying. When either of these chests are touched, Mourdred will emerge from below and attack the player.\nIt has Plagued, as well as either Orbiter or Mortar affixes. In addition, until it dies, it will continuously summon more Maggots to its side, in addition to its natural ability to grow them."}
