{"id": "9470", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9470", "title": "Mud Runner", "text": "Mud Runners are a variation of the &lt;a href=\"Horned%20Demon\"&gt;Horned Demon&lt;/a&gt;. They appear on the last level of the Catacombs and the first levels of the Caves. \nThough they are slightly weaker then their lesser kins, they have immunities and resistances. Their charge attack remains a serious threat, as it can do fire damage, which can be really dangerous to players with low resistances."}
{"id": "54603", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54603", "title": "Mulgaist the Molten", "text": " \n is a &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;, and a member of the &lt;a href=\"Dreadbirth\"&gt;Dreadbirth&lt;/a&gt;. \nLore.\nThe demon Mulgaist resides deep within an enormous volcano, slithering underneath a lake of lava. As of yet, no one has gotten close enough to the volcano to witness Mulgaist in its entirety, but their presence is made painfully aware through the plumes of magma that erupt from the volcano\u2019s maw. Villages surrounding the volcano hold charred &lt;a href=\"corpse\"&gt;bodies&lt;/a&gt; frozen in time, their hands held high in disbelief as Mulgaist set &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; to the rain.. \nReferences.\n "}
{"id": "29512", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29512", "title": "Mulliuqs the Horrid", "text": "Mulliuqs the Horrid, Timeless Overlord,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Barbed%20Lurker\"&gt;Barbed Lurker&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Ancient%20Ruins%20of%20Dholmour\"&gt;Ancient Ruins of Dholmour&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nIn combat, he has &lt;a href=\"Reflects%20Damage\"&gt;Reflects Damage&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Wormhole\"&gt;Wormhole&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Thunderstorm%20%28monster%20trait%29\"&gt;Thunderstorm&lt;/a&gt; traits. He is fought in three stages: every 25% &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt;, he becomes invulnerable and flees to the next platform, summoning &lt;a href=\"Scouring%20Charger\"&gt;Scouring Charger&lt;/a&gt;s and meteors (either molten or usual). At the final platform (near the entrance), he also summons Barbed Lurkers.\nA &lt;a href=\"bounty\"&gt;bounty&lt;/a&gt; may be assigned to kill Mulliuqs. Unlike most other \"kill bounties\", there is no secondary objective requiring killing additional enemies, presumably because he must be reached in a dungeon and his unusual encounter design."}
{"id": "19660", "revid": "3459498", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19660", "title": "Multi-Shot", "text": ""}
{"id": "5325", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5325", "title": "Multi-shot", "text": "Multi-shot is one of the possible bonuses &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique Monsters&lt;/a&gt; may obtain in &lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;. It only appears on monsters with ranged attacks and consists of two or more shots of that attack being fired at the same time.\nMonsters with both Multi-shot and &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20Enchanted\"&gt;Lightning Enchanted&lt;/a&gt; can be some of the most dangerous Unique Monsters in the game, especially on &lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; mode where one usually has poor resistances.\nMore powerful subspecies of &lt;a href=\"Quill%20Rat\"&gt;Quill Rat&lt;/a&gt;s, the thorned beasts, naturally possess a form of this attack. Amazons also access something similar with their &lt;a href=\"Multiple%20Shot\"&gt;Multiple Shot&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "19659", "revid": "3459498", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19659", "title": "Multi Shot", "text": ""}
{"id": "2084", "revid": "1773829", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2084", "title": "Multiplayer", "text": "Multiplayer is a &lt;a href=\"game%20mode\"&gt;game mode&lt;/a&gt; that allows you to play with more than one player in the game. Most \"Diablo\" content can be played in both single- and multiplayer modes. Multiplayer is of course required for &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt; combat, and is emphasized more by \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\".\nDiablo II.\nThere can be a maximum of eight players in a game. There are several options for multiplayer:\n/players X.\nAs of the 1.10 patch for Diablo II, it is possible to play the Single player mode in LoD with multiplayer difficulty: Open the Chat Box by pressing Enter, type /players X, where X is a number from 1 to 8, and press Enter. The message \"players set to X\" will display. Only newly spawned monsters will be affected.\nDisadvantages:\nAdvantages:\nThis adjustment is dangerous for builds that rely heavily on &lt;a href=\"Mana\"&gt;Mana&lt;/a&gt; during the low character levels.\nOn the other hand you can play on /players 8 from the very beginning, if you are careful.\nThe drop probability is so high, that you will run out of space to store all the &lt;a href=\"Gem\"&gt;Chipped Gems&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rune\"&gt;Rune&lt;/a&gt;s before you can get the &lt;a href=\"Horadric%20Cube\"&gt;Horadric Cube&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe gained XP per Monster is so high, that it's easily possible to reach e.g. Level 12 before fighting &lt;a href=\"Blood%20Raven\"&gt;Blood Raven&lt;/a&gt;, Level 20 before fighting &lt;a href=\"Andariel\"&gt;Andariel&lt;/a&gt; and Level 45 before fighting &lt;a href=\"Baal\"&gt;Baal&lt;/a&gt;. (All of this with \"/players 8\", still in &lt;a href=\"Normal%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Normal Difficulty&lt;/a&gt; and without reruns.)\nIt is possible, though not recommended, to change back to \"/players1\" before a major Boss is spawned. Fighting it would be much easier, but it will drop lower quantity and quality items compared to the previous play.\nDiablo III and beyond.\nSubsequent games are only played via &lt;a href=\"Battle.net\"&gt;Battle.net&lt;/a&gt;, removing local and direct networking options. Game sessions in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" and \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20IV\"&gt;Diablo IV&lt;/a&gt;\" can still be private or open to other players. \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\" is always played in a shared world with a higher emphasis on multiplayer and &lt;a href=\"PvP\"&gt;PvP&lt;/a&gt;, but with some instanced content that may be played single- or multiplayer.\n&lt;a href=\"Solo%20Self%20Found\"&gt;Solo Self Found&lt;/a&gt; mode was added to \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" towards the end of active development for the game, for a categorically single-player challenge."}
{"id": "2134", "revid": "48080954", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2134", "title": "Multiple Shot", "text": "Multiple Shot is an &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"Legend has it that the fabled Amazon archer, &lt;a href=\"Palashia\"&gt;Palashia&lt;/a&gt;, bragged in her youth that she could best the combined skills of all her greatest rivals. Taking umbrage, her rivals gathered to challenge her outrageous boast, arranging a contest to decide the question. To preserve her honor, Palashia was to strike the targets of all her rivals before they could land a single arrow. When dawn arose on the day of the contest, Palashia stood ready with her bow. At the signal, her rivals nocked their arrows and loosed a volley towards their targets. Palashia gathered her energies, and let fly with her own, single arrow. To the amazement of onlookers, her arrow split into many, cleaving the arrows of her rivals, and moving on to strike every target directly in their centers. This mysterious technique quickly became a martial secret that only the finest archers are able to master. \"\nGeneral Information.\nSynergies.\nMultiple Shot is a skill which as its name states allows the &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; to fire off more than one arrow. While being a good skill for damage over a large area, it only deals 3/4ths of normal attack damage (this includes elemental damage) and only 1 arrow may hit each enemy, making it a bad choice for attacking single, tough opponents. The penalty still applies to versions below 1.10, but it does not say on the skill, and is visible on the character stats menu when Multiple Shot is selected.\nAlthough v2.6 claims that it \"Fixed the tooltip for\u00a0 Multiple Shot to reflect the synergy bonus\", as of v2.7 it's in fact still wrong. The actual formula used for calculation is dam*3/4*(100%+bonuses), including the synergy bonus like it would +X % damage from an offhand mod or Dex. This can be verified by looking directly at the dam in the char stats; with e.g. 3 lvl Guided Arrow, the damage is shown as \"111% Weapon Damage\", but can be observed as lower than base damage from a normal attack still - similarly, even with e.g. 11 lvl Guided Arrow and some Dexterity, the damage will still be lower than 2x the base. \nThe player can control the spread angle of the volley using the distance between the point clicked and the character herself \u2014 clicking far away from the character results in a narrower, more focused volley, while clicking close to the character results in a much wider spread.\nAside from actual arrow damage, &lt;a href=\"Life%20Steal\"&gt;leeching&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Deadly%20Strike\"&gt;Deadly Strike&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Critical%20Strike\"&gt;Critical Strike&lt;/a&gt; works with every arrow, but everything else (procs, &lt;a href=\"crushing%20blow\"&gt;crushing blow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"knockback\"&gt;knockback&lt;/a&gt;, et cetera) only triggers from the center two arrows.\nEach extra skill point in this skill increases the number of arrows fired by 1, but also increases the mana cost by 1 as well. When the skill level is fairly high already, one may find that increasing the volley by one arrow makes little to no difference, and after level 23 there isn't any increase (the skill is hard-capped to fire at most 24 arrows). Points placed after level 23 only increase the mana cost with no advantage whatsoever (not counting synergies to other skills)."}
{"id": "16721", "revid": "3423357", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=16721", "title": "Multiple Shot (magic suffix)", "text": "Multiple Shot is a &lt;a href=\"suffix\"&gt;suffix&lt;/a&gt; that can appear on &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;. It provides &lt;a href=\"Charged%20item\"&gt;charges&lt;/a&gt; of the skill &lt;a href=\"Multiple%20Shot\"&gt;Multiple Shot&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt can start spawning on items at &lt;a href=\"Item%20Level\"&gt;Item Level&lt;/a&gt; 18, but will not be able to spawn on all items until level 63.\nStats.\n\"Can appear on:\" &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Items\"&gt;Magic Items&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Rare%20Items\"&gt;Rare Items&lt;/a&gt;\n\"Is available on:\" &lt;a href=\"Amazon%20Weapons\"&gt;Amazon Weapons&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bows\"&gt;Bows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crossbows\"&gt;Crossbows&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gloves\"&gt;Gloves&lt;/a&gt;"}
{"id": "19658", "revid": "13298744", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=19658", "title": "Multishot", "text": ""}
{"id": "24401", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=24401", "title": "Multishot (Diablo III)", "text": "Multishot (a.k.a. Multi-shot or Multiple Shot) is an Archery \u00a0skill, based on the similar &lt;a href=\"Amazon\"&gt;Amazon&lt;/a&gt; skill from \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\". Unlike its predecessor, it increases damage compared to an individual shot.\nIn-game.\nReleases a volley of arrows, hitting all enemies in a large cone (roughly 60 degrees wide and 75 yards long) for &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; damage. Notably, it is not affected by the &lt;a href=\"Missile%20Dampening\"&gt;Missile Dampening&lt;/a&gt; affix on Elites."}
