{"id": "3450", "revid": "47915220", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3450", "title": "Mummy Sarcophagus", "text": "The Mummy Sarcophagus spawns &lt;a href=\"Mummy\"&gt;Mummies&lt;/a&gt; that act as guardians of treasures. However, the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt;'s influence has infused these protectors with a hunger for human flesh. It is of the utmost importance to destroy these Sarcophagi at once, as many mummies are capable of appearing in a few seconds. Unfortunately, the destruction of the Mummy Sarcophague is a very lengthy process due to its immense durability. &lt;a href=\"Life\"&gt;Life&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mana\"&gt;Mana&lt;/a&gt; cannot be stolen from them and they do not drop any items upon their destruction. They are found in various tombs and can spawn only &lt;a href=\"Dried%20Corpse\"&gt;Dried Corpses&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn Hell difficulty, Mummy Sarcophagi are immune to &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt;.\nA good way to counter Sarcophagi is by standing directly in front of the door (as close to the sarcophagus as possible): this will block the exit and prevent additional &lt;a href=\"Mummy\"&gt;mummies&lt;/a&gt; from spawning.\nStatistics.\nDevelopment.\nOriginally in v1.00-1.09d Mummy Sarcophagus could spawn different mummy types depending on location. \nIn v1.10 it was changed to spawn only Dried Corpses, probably because stronger mummy types in infinite numbers would be overwhelming to battle."}
{"id": "28759", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28759", "title": "Mundunogo", "text": "Mundunogo, Bad Medicine Chieftain,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; found in the &lt;a href=\"Dahlgur%20Oasis\"&gt;Dahlgur Oasis&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nMundunogo always spawns at the wooden construct area, on the bridge with moving cogwheels.\nIn combat, he has Teleporter and Fast affixes."}
