{"id": "54396", "revid": "50366882", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=54396", "title": "Nadya", "text": " Nadya is an &lt;a href=\"amazon\"&gt;amazon&lt;/a&gt; hailing from &lt;a href=\"Skartara\"&gt;Skartara&lt;/a&gt;. At a time, she participated in the burden run of &lt;a href=\"Philios%20Games\"&gt;Philios Games&lt;/a&gt;. Though she'd trained for years for the event, her kindness caused her to lose the race.\nBiography.\nAfter years of training, Nadya joined in the burden run to the base of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Karcheus\"&gt;Karcheus&lt;/a&gt;. Her island of &lt;a href=\"Skartara\"&gt;Skartara&lt;/a&gt; had rarely won, but victors commanded glory, &lt;a href=\"gold\"&gt;gold&lt;/a&gt; and station upon &lt;a href=\"Twin%20Seas\"&gt;the seas&lt;/a&gt;. Many of the repeat contestants from &lt;a href=\"Philios\"&gt;Philios&lt;/a&gt; wore resplendent &lt;a href=\"armor\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt; with symbols of their villages, heavy laden to show their strength. Nadya's armor was lean and unornamented.\nAt the start of the race, Nadya kept pace with her competitors over the leaf-littered floor of the jungle. Suddenly, it began to rain heavily. While the forest floor surged and soil cascaded beneath them, runners wearing the heaviest armor fell, and were trampled by those behind. By then, Nadya was taking the lead. \nFrom her position, Nadya was a mere league from Karcheus. She saw cruel joy in the faces of the other lead runners as they sped away from the injured. They did not even look back as she slowed. The others streamed past Nadya as she helped fallen runners from the mud. She reached Karcheus last, won no gold or titles, and was uncelebrated in her village. Nadya no longer cared, her pride was unwavering.\nLegacy.\nThe victorious racers of Philios carried their triumphs to sea as soldiers, and took up positions of influence above their peers. They spoke boldly of their competition, and argued fruitlessly about which of them had run the most perfect race. Meanwhile, Skartara never acknowledged Nadya's participation, yet this did not shake her confidence. Victory in the eyes of others is longer-lasting than victory alone, but it is hardly eternal.\nIn-game.\nNadya is mentioned in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", in the flavor text of \"&lt;a href=\"Windloft%20Perfection\"&gt;Windloft Perfection&lt;/a&gt;\" &lt;a href=\"item%20set\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt;."}
