{"id": "28397", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=28397", "title": "Nalghban the Foul", "text": "Nalghban the Foul,\u00a0Dark Moon Clan Elder Shaman, is a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Unique\"&gt;Super Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Khazra%20Shaman\"&gt;Khazra Shaman&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\nHe appears during the &lt;a href=\"Trailing%20the%20Coven\"&gt;Trailing the Coven&lt;/a&gt; quest, jumping out of the ground together with four &lt;a href=\"Khazra\"&gt;Khazra&lt;/a&gt; after the player loots the Sacred Khazra Staff from &lt;a href=\"Karyna%27s%20Lost%20Wagon\"&gt;Karyna's Lost Wagon&lt;/a&gt;. Killing him is not required for the quest.\nIn combat, he has Electrified and Illusionist affix, and shoots &lt;a href=\"Lightning\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; bolts instead of regular &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt; spheres."}
{"id": "41121", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41121", "title": "Namari", "text": "Namari is a &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nLong before the destruction of the &lt;a href=\"Worldstone\"&gt;Worldstone&lt;/a&gt;, Namari and her fellow nephalem defeated &lt;a href=\"Sargoth\"&gt;Sargoth&lt;/a&gt;, a fellow nephalem who had betrayed them, allying with &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Hells\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt;. He was sealed in a &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Namari\"&gt;temple&lt;/a&gt;. However, his power grew, and Namari confronted him in single combat, but was defeated, though Sargoth remained trapped inside. Namari's &lt;a href=\"soul\"&gt;soul&lt;/a&gt; was bound to the temple to ensure that Sargoth never escaped.\nOver the millennia, the power of the &lt;a href=\"nephalem\"&gt;nephalem&lt;/a&gt; waned, while Sargoth's power continued to grow. In &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231270\"&gt;1270&lt;/a&gt;, the last of the temple's three beacons were stolen, rendering Namari powerless. Later, she was summoned by the &lt;a href=\"Wizard\"&gt;Wizard&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Jin\"&gt;Jin&lt;/a&gt;, who was accompanied by a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;hero/group of heroes&lt;/a&gt;. Namari told them about Sargoth and of the missing beacons. If they were returned, they could stop Sargoth before it was too late. If they aided her, she would give them the objects they sought out.\nThe heroes returned with the beacons, much to Namari's joy. She ordered Jin to stay at the altar in case Sargoth broke the seal before they were ready, while she led the other hero(es) into the temple. Her spirit ached at the sight of the temple's interior, but nevertheless, guided the champion(s) to the final chamber, where they slew Sargoth.\nIn-game.\nNamari appears as an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\". She first appears in the &lt;a href=\"quest\"&gt;quest&lt;/a&gt; \"&lt;a href=\"Overgrown%20Temple\"&gt;Overgrown Temple&lt;/a&gt;\" in the exterior of the &lt;a href=\"Temple%20of%20Namari\"&gt;Temple of Namari&lt;/a&gt;. Later, she guides the player through the player's interior, in the Temple of Namari &lt;a href=\"dungeon%20%28Diablo%20Immortal%29\"&gt;dungeon&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "44794", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=44794", "title": "Nan", "text": "Nan was a servant of &lt;a href=\"the%20Countess\"&gt;the Countess&lt;/a&gt; before her overthrow.\nBiography.\nAncestry.\nNan\u2019s mother was a distant cousin to the family who lived in the &lt;a href=\"Big%20House\"&gt;Big House&lt;/a&gt;, and served as a lady-in-waiting to the mother of &lt;a href=\"the%20Countess\"&gt;the Countess&lt;/a&gt;. She fell in love with a blacksmith, and went to live in the swamps.\nEarly Life.\nNan grew up in the marshes of northern &lt;a href=\"Khanduras\"&gt;Khanduras&lt;/a&gt;. It was a hard life. As a child, her granfer (her father\u2019s father) told her that the noble family who ruled from the &lt;a href=\"Big%20House\"&gt;Big House&lt;/a&gt; practiced bride-theft and groom-theft. She could believe it, but found it easier to believe that the family married themselves and kin and cousins in order to keep their bloodline pure. Her granfer also discouraged her from preening, for in the swamp, becauty was both a snare and a foxlight.\nNan was taught how to read and write, due to her mother\u2019s noble origins. Her granfer loved her, but despised her mother. Nan did most of the work in the house, maintaining it, and oiling her father\u2019s tools, while her parents mooned over each other.\nWhen Nan was around 15/16 years old, her mother died, and her father died the year after that, as according to Nan, he loved his wife far more than his daughter, and with his wife dead, there was nothing left to live for.\nIn Service to the Countess.\nFirst Meetings.\nAt the age of eighteen, Nan\u2019s fortunes changed. The Countess, two years her junior, had seen her outside the Big House, and had taken a fancy to Nan\u2019s looks. Her granfer informed her that she was wanted as a servant in the Big House, to which Nan refused. He pleaded, as did her neighbors, for no-one wanted the wrath of the noble family brought down on them. A man came down from the Big House every day for a sennight, cozening or begging or threatening, before at last, the Countess herself came down, mounted on a horse. She rode up to Nan\u2019s house.\nNan was entranced with the Countess\u2019s beauty and mannerisms, but still refused, at least at first. The Countess mixed compliments and insults alike, until finally, Nan relented, saying that she\u2019d come, but leave at the end of spring if things didn\u2019t suit her. \nThe First Two Years.\nAfter escaping the Old House, Nan\u2019s role in the Countess\u2019s actions was hazy. Because the clergy were unable to talk any sense, they couldn\u2019t implicate her. A number of crofters wanted to burn Nan at the stake, but her granfer spoke in her defense. Nan lied, and said she knew nothing of the murdered girls. Whether they believed it or not was irrelevant, as the villagers prepared to storm the keep at sunrise.\nNan wrote her testimony. She understood that it was likely she would be hanged, and considered herself guilty. However, even then, she could not abandon her love for the Countess. \nPersonality and Traits.\nNan rarely used her birthname (\u201cNan\u201d was a nickname used by the Countess).\nNan considered herself \u201cvery pretty for what [she] was,\u201d with roses in her cheeks, and was not pallid like the other girls of the swamps. However, she was taught not to flaunt her appearance. She was \u201cstrong as a little horse.\u201d She had black hair and blue eyes.\nShe disliked priests and clergy. By the end of her service to the Countess, she was consumed with self-loathing."}
{"id": "52966", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=52966", "title": "Nan Jiang", "text": "Nan Jiang is a senior game designer for \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\"."}
{"id": "45059", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=45059", "title": "Nangari", "text": "The nangari (a.k.a. snake men) are a group of snake-like &lt;a href=\"monster\"&gt;monster&lt;/a&gt;s found in &lt;a href=\"Hawezar\"&gt;Hawezar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nahantu\"&gt;Nahantu&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nNangari are twisted amalgamations of multiple snake heads, even &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; body parts. Not content with simply killing their prey, they seem to take a malicious pleasure from inflicting as much suffering as possible before &lt;a href=\"death\"&gt;death&lt;/a&gt;. They keep humans as thralls, and can even consume a human body whole.\nThe nangari are in perpetual conflict with &lt;a href=\"Druids\"&gt;Druids&lt;/a&gt; in Hawezar. Some in Hawezar do not fear the nangari but admire them, and seek to leverage the beasts' gifts for their own ends."}
{"id": "33677", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=33677", "title": "Narthal", "text": "Narthal was a member of the &lt;a href=\"Bear%20Tribe\"&gt;Bear Tribe&lt;/a&gt;. While travelling through the &lt;a href=\"Dreadlands\"&gt;Dreadlands&lt;/a&gt;, he discovered the aftermath of a great battle. He did not recognize the dead, but noticed that many had filed their teeth to points. Among the debris of the battle, he found a &lt;a href=\"Cuirass%20of%20the%20Wastes\"&gt;piece of armor&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "41738", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=41738", "title": "Nash", "text": "Nash is an NPC in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20Immortal\"&gt;Diablo Immortal&lt;/a&gt;\", appearing in &lt;a href=\"Wynton%27s%20Grand%20Market\"&gt;Wynton's Grand Market&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Westmarch%20%28City%29\"&gt;Westmarch&lt;/a&gt;. He can be seen trying to get &lt;a href=\"Dya\"&gt;Dya&lt;/a&gt;'s attention (and failing)."}
{"id": "29533", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=29533", "title": "Nashok", "text": "Nashok, Koghar's Partner,\u00a0is a &lt;a href=\"Unique%20Monsters\"&gt;Unique&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Bogan%20Trapper\"&gt;Bogan Trapper&lt;/a&gt; found in &lt;a href=\"The%20Hunter%27s%20Den\"&gt;The Hunter's Den&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\". He spawns when players touch his &lt;a href=\"Maggot%20Brood\"&gt;trophies&lt;/a&gt;. Only one of the two (&lt;a href=\"Koghar\"&gt;Koghar&lt;/a&gt; or Nashok) will appear.\nIn combat, he has Electrified, Desecrator and Nightmarish affixes. His retinue of &lt;a href=\"Boggit\"&gt;Boggit&lt;/a&gt;s and Trappers also comes to his aid."}
{"id": "1681", "revid": "58609", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=1681", "title": "Natalya", "text": "Natalya is a former &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt;-turned &lt;a href=\"Demon%20Hunter\"&gt;Demon Hunter&lt;/a&gt;.\nBiography.\nKurast.\nNatalya was in &lt;a href=\"Kurast\"&gt;Kurast&lt;/a&gt; during the &lt;a href=\"Timeline%231263\"&gt;time&lt;/a&gt; of the awakening of the &lt;a href=\"Prime%20Evils\"&gt;Prime Evils&lt;/a&gt;. She arrived and waited for further orders. During that time, she rejected an offer from &lt;a href=\"Asheara\"&gt;Asheara&lt;/a&gt; to join the &lt;a href=\"Iron%20Wolves\"&gt;Iron Wolves&lt;/a&gt;, and talked to &lt;a href=\"Hratli\"&gt;Hratli&lt;/a&gt; about weapons. She made many around her uneasy, due to her intimidating presence, skepticism, cold attitude and mysterious aura; many considered her a quiet, yet strange person. &lt;a href=\"Deckard%20Cain\"&gt;Deckard Cain&lt;/a&gt; in particular was wary of her presence due to her being a mage hunter, wondering what her true purpose in Kurast could be.\nA week after her arrival, she encountered a &lt;a href=\"Classes%23Diablo%20II\"&gt;group of heroes&lt;/a&gt; who were in pursuit of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Wanderer\"&gt;Dark Wanderer&lt;/a&gt;. She provided them with information, but could not help further, as she was obliged to stay at the docks to await further orders. By the time the group defeated &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt;, she had left the area to head north into the lands.\nDealing with Demons.\nA few years before the &lt;a href=\"End%20of%20Days\"&gt;End of Days&lt;/a&gt;, Natalya left the Viz-Jaq'taar, instead taking up the cause of the Demon Hunters, seeking redemption. She focused on the hunting of &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s, gaining some small semblance of peace from doing so.\nIn-game.\nDiablo II.\nNatalya appears as an &lt;a href=\"NPC\"&gt;NPC&lt;/a&gt; in of \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\", found in the &lt;a href=\"Kurast%20Docks\"&gt;Kurast Docks&lt;/a&gt;. Despite a shared class, she has no unique dialogue for an &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; character. She serves no purpose for the storyline and has no quests related to her, but does offer exposition about her Order, gossip and some minor quest info.\nShe disappears from the area right after &lt;a href=\"Mephisto\"&gt;Mephisto&lt;/a&gt; is slain. According to her dialogue for when \"\" is completed (which the player never hears due to her disappearing), she received new orders to head to the Northern Steppes, but wouldn't say why. Despite that, Natalya is not found during Act V nor mentioned again.\nThe item set, &lt;a href=\"Natalya%27s%20Odium\"&gt;Natalya's Odium&lt;/a&gt;, is named after her.\nDiablo III.\n&lt;a href=\"Natalya%27s%20Vengeance\"&gt;Natalya's Vengeance&lt;/a&gt; is an &lt;a href=\"item%20set\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\", used by Demon Hunters. The items' description provide vague hints at her activities post-\"Diablo II\", revealing that she abandoned the Viz-Jaq'taar, leaving her days as a mage slayer behind, and became a Demon Hunter instead."}
