{"id": "23218", "revid": "50840914", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=23218", "title": "Natalya's Vengeance", "text": "Natalya's Vengeance (previously Natalya's Solace) is an &lt;a href=\"Set%20Items\"&gt;item set&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\".\u00a0\nThis set is named for &lt;a href=\"Natalya\"&gt;Natalya&lt;/a&gt;, a former &lt;a href=\"Assassin\"&gt;Assassin&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Viz-Jaq%27taar\"&gt;Viz-Jaq'taar&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe set requires a character level of 60, and can only drop on &lt;a href=\"Torment%20%28difficulty%29\"&gt;Torment&lt;/a&gt; difficulty.\nUp until patch 2.7.4, the set formed the heart of a &lt;a href=\"Rain%20of%20Vengeance\"&gt;Rain of Vengeance&lt;/a&gt;-centered build. However, with the &lt;a href=\"Season\"&gt;Season&lt;/a&gt; 28 patch 2.7.5, the focus of the set was shifted to a &lt;a href=\"Spike%20Trap\"&gt;Spike Trap&lt;/a&gt;-&lt;a href=\"Caltrops\"&gt;Caltrops&lt;/a&gt; combo build. It is the only Demon Hunter set that can be combined with both &lt;a href=\"Captain%20Crimson%27s%20Trimmings\"&gt;Captain Crimson's Trimmings&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Aughild%27s%20Authority\"&gt;Aughild's Authority&lt;/a&gt; through the &lt;a href=\"Ring%20of%20Royal%20Grandeur\"&gt;Ring of Royal Grandeur&lt;/a&gt;, and as such, one of the most powerful.\nPieces.\nThe set consists of seven pieces, six of which are required to complete it. Two of them, the cloak and crossbow, are Demon Hunter-restricted.\nSet Bonus prior to patch 2.7.5:\nThe first bonus only triggers if a Primary skill (&lt;a href=\"Grenades\"&gt;Grenades&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Hungering%20Arrow\"&gt;Hungering Arrow&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Evasive%20Fire\"&gt;Evasive Fire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Bolas\"&gt;Bolas&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Entangling%20Shot\"&gt;Entangling Shot&lt;/a&gt;) or a damaging skill that costs Hatred actually hits an enemy, and only once per cast.\nThe second bonus is multiplicative to other similar modifiers, and applies even to the &lt;a href=\"Crashing%20Rain\"&gt;Crashing Rain&lt;/a&gt; beast.\nThe last bonus does not stack from multiple applications, but does affect the cast that triggered it.\nDevelopment.\nPrior to patch 2.2.0, this set also provided bonuses to &lt;a href=\"Dexterity\"&gt;Dexterity&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Critical%20Hit\"&gt;Critical Hit&lt;/a&gt; Chance and maximum &lt;a href=\"Discipline\"&gt;Discipline&lt;/a&gt;."}
