{"id": "9369", "revid": "839260", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9369", "title": "Natural Resistance", "text": ""}
{"id": "3564", "revid": "1088621", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3564", "title": "Natural Resistance (Diablo II)", "text": "Natural Resistance is a &lt;a href=\"Barbarian%20%28Diablo%20II%29\"&gt;Barbarian&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Skill\"&gt;Skill&lt;/a&gt; in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20II\"&gt;Diablo II&lt;/a&gt;\".\nLore.\n\"In order to survive the unforgiving lands of the north, the people of the Barbarian tribes have developed hardy resistances to the common elements. Heat and cold alike are something they endure often. Since food is scarce while foraging, they have learned to consume species of plants that would slay normal men. Through additional training, a warrior can fortify himself further against these dangers, allowing him to better survive while traveling to unfamiliar lands and battling unknown foes.\"\nGeneral Information.\nNatural Resistance is the final passive skill, making him more resistant against &lt;a href=\"Fire\"&gt;Fire&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Cold\"&gt;Cold&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lightning%20%28damage%29\"&gt;Lightning&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Poison\"&gt;Poison&lt;/a&gt; damage (but not &lt;a href=\"Physical\"&gt;Physical&lt;/a&gt; and not &lt;a href=\"Magic%20Damage\"&gt;Magic&lt;/a&gt;). It is a very useful skill at higher difficulties, where better resistances are paramount.\nThe benefits from this skill suffers from diminishing returns per point, so putting just one point into it and taking advantage of skill-boosting equipment for a little more resistance may prove more efficient. The boost at low levels is much smaller than that provided by the &lt;a href=\"Paladin\"&gt;Paladin&lt;/a&gt;'s &lt;a href=\"Salvation\"&gt;Salvation&lt;/a&gt; skill (which starts at 60% at level 1), but unlike Salvation, Natural Resistance provides a permanent bonus, and offers protection against Poison damage, which Salvation doesn't.\nWhile Natural Resistance helps bolster resistances, it cannot be a complete substitute for equipment that boosts resistances due to its limitations. This is even more evident in the expansion, due to the increased penalties for &lt;a href=\"Nightmare%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Nightmare&lt;/a&gt;/&lt;a href=\"Hell%20%28Difficulty%29\"&gt;Hell&lt;/a&gt; difficulty; if a Barbarian were to max out this skill in classic Diablo II, he would have +17% all resistances in Hell difficulty."}
{"id": "9294", "revid": "24916843", "url": "https://diablo.fandom.com/wiki?curid=9294", "title": "Natural Resistance (Diablo III)", "text": "Natural Resistance was a skill in \"&lt;a href=\"Diablo%20III\"&gt;Diablo III&lt;/a&gt;\" alpha. It would increase all &lt;a href=\"resistances\"&gt;resistances&lt;/a&gt; by +10.\nIn the released game, &lt;a href=\"Superstition\"&gt;Superstition&lt;/a&gt; fulfills a similar role."}
